,Recommended,265300,22791610,"Posted: 4 May, 2016",all,|Z.N.| ArcticElysium |USA|,"Lords Of The Fallen ReviewI personally really like this title. Now, before I dive deep into this review I just want to clarify a few things.I had originally played this around November of 2014 on Xbox One. I think it ran at about 15 - 30 FPS. So I didn't see it worth it on Console.I never made it past the second boss a.k.a ""Commander"" while playing this on console because there was no difficulty option.I have waited until 2016 to pick it up because I bought a GTX 970 paired with my AMD FX-6300 so I can play it on PC.I haven't completed the game, because I am taking my time with it and exploring everywhere I can.Pros:Beautiful graphics.Good level designs.Sounds! The sounds are amazing in the game. From the footsteps of your plated boots hitting the ground to opening a demon chest and hearing it ""roar"" until completely opened.Options menu. I would have liked to see more, but what they have now is fineThe ""Feel"" of the game. I love how heavy you can feel when wearing heavy armor and how light and agile you are when wearing cloth ""rouge"" armor.Weapons. There are plenty of weapons to choose from and having certain runes slotted into them makes the weapons more deadly!Looting. Oh man, looting in this game is so much fun! From looting armor, weapons and runes I can't get enough!Mixed:Combat. While the combat is somewhat balanced, it just feels ""okay"". We do have some special moves you can pull of depending on your orientation to the enemy and/or type of attack, I think is kinda boring. I've spent most my time with the following on every enemy. 2 Heavy attacks + 1 Regular + 1 Heavy.AI. The AI in this game gives me a mixed feeling. The AI scales with your characters level so it makes sense to make them hard or challenging. Well, with the different types of enemies you encounter (Excluding bosses) I feel like some of them ""cheat"" or are more difficult than they should be.Music. (The Pros about sound were specifically on the in-game sound design, not the music) The music is okay, while it's nothing great, it does provide a certain feeling. I just wish they had a little more variety. While playing through the game you'll find yourself listening to the same audio tracks over and over again.Cons:Boss fights. I am a few bosses in and had the weapon ""My Axe"" and the ""Symmetry"" armor set. While wearing this armor you get a 15% (I think) Damage increased when two-handing a weapon. So, I had two runes added to ""My Axe"" one High Poison Rune and one Low Fire Rune. I literally hit the ""Annihilator"" Boss about 6 times and killed it. Certain bosses are hard and certain ones are too easy and predictable.Characters. I really dislike how all the character are introduced. Harkyn, a criminal we know that, but what for? Why was he chosen by Kaslo just to help ""save"" the world? Kalso, No idea who he is, besides a wizard/mage that was travelling with Harkyn and broke him out of prison. Anntanas, the guards look up to him as if he is a god. No real back story to him. (Keep in mind this is based off of not finding every single audio note and a general play-through of the game)_____________________________________________________________________________________________________Overall is a nice game. It's solid and is worth picking it up. I personally waited until it was on sale from $39.99 to $9.99 USD. I would spend $9.99 again on it in a heart beat.So, if you want to play dark souls or have tried and it seems too difficult for you then just pick this up. It's a much more relaxed casual look on a ""Hardcore"" Action RPG.Rating 8/10."
76561197972720910,Recommended,265300,23105538,"Posted: 20 May, 2016",all,MaYzE,"Not sure what graphics engine they used, but this game was pretty.  I really enjoyed my play though with this game.  Some frustration with slow attack animations, but nothing game breaking.  I had read sites saying that this game considered easy mode Dark Souls, and I would have to agree.  Although it was still challenging at times, I did find as you got new gear the difficulty went way down.Like most games, you will get a feel for a certain way of attacking, certain combos, and spells to use.  Once you master your technique this game is not very challenging but still wickedly fun.  This title may not have the depth, challenge, and longevity of the souls games, but for someone looking for a moderately challenging and beautiful ARPG this is a worthy pickup.  I would suggest anyone who is not familiar with action RPG titles play this one before attempting Dark Souls to understand some of the battle mechanics and frustrations that come with ARPG games.  Most definitely recommended."
