sin and I felt fed up (2 out of 4 assassin’s skills are almost exactly the same as warrior’s) + the only thing NG+ changes is the enemies health what means you just need to hit them more like in Fallout 4, sponges-	(All the) Bosses are like super-easy; no challenge there at all; The most it took me to take down a boss was 2 tries and I had to do it only with 3 bosses. The biggest let-down was the last boss. I entered a room for the first time with just 4 potions (out of 12) and I won... It took me like 15 minutes, being careful with my life but it was just… too easy-	The story climax and the ending was disappointing; [SPOILERS WARNING]  first off why did I have to betray humans and Antannas? Why couldn’t I fight the god and help Antannas? No choice there and I was expecting more. Ending itself was poor as well.-	Monsters variety – not enough and too boringBut despite all the above I would still recommend this game to anyone to try it out. It was fun for me for one play through and the game has a lot of nice touches to offer (like graphics, atomosphere, secrets and lore). For me it is strong 6/10. After finishing it I can say (no remorse) it is in different league than Dark Souls; it is a different game but in the same time feels a bit short and lacking in some aspects where Dark Souls shines."
