76561198123395143,Recommended,265300,28108138,"Posted: 30 November, 2016",all,Random Task,"Considering that i'm a little more than halfway through the game now, I guess it's about time I wrote a review for it. And I have to admit: it's one of the finest RPG's I have ever played. I stayed away from it for a while because I got involved in Dark Souls, but I think that this game is better than Dark Souls And Dark Souls 2.This game definitely does not deserve the negative attention that it is getting because of performance issues. Well, if anybody had taken the time to look into the settings, having the shadows set to low will fix many of these problems. And you can't say it works fine for me because I have a fancy computer; All i've got right now is a GTX 760 and an AMD Phenom ii x4 820, and on high settings (aside form shadows) I get 60 frames/second consistantly without experiencing game crashes.Enough said about my computer, here's what I think of the game itself: Never once have I felt bored with this game so far. Many people would compare this game to the Souls games, saying that this game is terrible. In reality, as I mentioned before, it's better than the first 2 Souls games. Nothing can beat Dark Souls 3, but did it really have to take them Demon's Souls and 2 more games to figure out how these games are supposed to work? I'm not saying that the souls games are bad, it's just that this is better. Realistically, there could be a larger variatey of enemies and more classes to chose from, but it's the gameplay itself that got me hooked. How there are multiple NPC'S for you to interact with and actually respond to is what makes the story engaging. And these NPC""S have their own emotions and personalities as well. And as for the combat- there couldn't be anything better. The control is smoother than it is in any other RPG I have played (other people say that the controls are clunky because they are probably not familiar with this type of game). The hit detection is precice, and every battle you come across has life to it- even if it is just 1 enemy you are facing.As a final note, if you have played and BEAT a Dark Souls game or Bloodborne, then you sould only get this game if you want a more relaxed experience, as this is easier than those games. It still has it's difficulties, but overall it is less stressful playing this game. If you have NEVER played a souls game, then this is the place to start. Overall, it's easier and more enjoyable, and it has more story involved in it.And my final thought is that this game has one thing that I have always wanted to see in a souls game: YOU CAN SAVE YOUR PROGRESS WITHOUT SPAWNING ENEMIES!!!"
