76561198021260579,Recommended,265300,21998091,"Posted: 23 March, 2016",all,Aodyri,"A few technical problems with this one. If you are using an AMD graphics card, this game will likely slow down or run at sub optimum. The specs required are higher than suggested. It isn't super stable.That said, this game is a solid experience. Like many people, I will compare it to Dark Souls since they fit in the same niche. This game is an odd blend of Diablo style leveling & loot collection (everything is randomized), and Dark Souls combat.You can technically pick a class, but very quickly these have little to no difference, beyond the cleric having a heal. Weapon stats, damage, and speed are all random so a pair of shortswords can do more damage than a two hander, and be slower. You have a stamina bar, health, a limited number of health potions that refill at rest points, a block, parry, heavy attack, light attack, and roll.The art personally reminds me of the chunky comic book style from Darksiders, so a big plus. It does repeat the Dark Souls 2 problem of most enemies being some variation of ""guy in armor"", but they all look impressive, and the rarer non-human enemies are quite cool. The story is pretty standard fantasy fluff, and isn't going to under or overwhelm anyone. For 20$ or less, you are getting 10+ hours of solid game to slake that thirst that -for me- only the Souls series really fills."
76561198060384351,Recommended,265300,31813480,Posted: 17 May,all,Bob the Skeleton,"This game is okay. The combat and appearence of the game resembles Dark Souls at first glance but after some time playing the game you figure out that that is not the case. The combat is fun at first but clunky when you really get into the thick of it. The ""fat roll"" in LotF is still managable so there's no reason not to max out your weight. The bosses can be challenging but some end up feeling more like meat sponges than enemies. While there were three character classes in the game only one of them felt relevant to the gameplay, with the Rogue class being an honorable mention at best and the Mage being somewhat useless (in the time I spent playing it). Being only single player is alright, even though it might've been better as a co-op game (either summons like Dark Souls or some other co-op system) with an optional single player experience. Overall the game can be fun but make sure to only pick it up on sale."
