76561198062443975,Recommended,265300,14415151,"Posted: 10 February, 2015",all,Zoinks,"Let me start off by saying that Lords of the Fallen is a great game.The graphics are amazing and the experience is even further enhanced by impressively gritty sound effects. The combat is weighty and more complex than you may think based on whatever youtube videos or live streams you have seen. There are numerous ways to cut up your enemies, be it with an axe, sword, mace or even a bloody polesword. Combining light and heavy attacks has varying results, which is complimented by dodging and sprinting attacks.Now, there are a couple important points I'd like to make, first regarding the claims of extreme game-breaking bugs and the second to its comparison to the Dark Souls franchise.The bugs: After its release I am sure this game had numerous game breaking bugs; however I purchased the game recently and have only experienced a couple minor bugs that were fixed in a minute. I've had only had to restart the game once to fix a bug and that was because I was assumed a setting change that I had done would only work when restarting the game and it did. I am now about 10 hours into the game, 5 bosses down and have not have ONE crash. NOT ONE. So people, please start buying this game and get stuck in !Even better is its pause mechanic, which comes into play when minimizing. I have a fairly powerful gaming laptop (Lenovo Y510p), but some games do overheat such as this. When it gets hot, however, the game simply minimizes instead of crashes and when it does it PAUSES. So i have never died from an unwanted minimize.NOW - DARK SOULS...................... I can't believe the publics reaction to it being like dark souls. As someone who has beated Dark Souls and Dark Souls 2 I can easily say that this game is a treat. Yes they are similar, but that's a good thing. Lords is merely inspired by the game and it really does differ greatly. Yes it has that timing-orientated combat, the powerful monster enemies and the bosses that can crush you. But it is not Dark Souls and varies greatly. It does include some aspects of Darksiders (although I never thought I'd admit this) in terms of graphics and the fact that in Dark Souls your aim is to not get hit and its pretty easy, but in Lords of the Fallen sometimes the best strategy is to take a few hits while jumping axe swinging into the enemey because you know thats his biggest opening (the tower shield guys)First, the good:The ability to pause in game to either the home screen or your inventory. At first I thought this was a bit too much as it was something I had come to appreciate when playing Dark Souls, but then I realized how insanely irritating it was to not be able to pause in Dark Souls.Combat is powerful, complex, weighty and rewarding.Amazing current-gen graphicsGreat music and sound effectsIntricately designed areas and worldBosses that are definitely fun and well thought outLabyrinthian Diablo like dungeonsCut scenese with customizable dialouge and ""last hit kill"" cutscenes, which I felt were a niceish touchEach weapon has a unique and sick backstab actionThe bad:The bosses are sometimes too easy (e.g worshipper was great. Infiltrator was boring)Some bugsMaybe not enough 'outside' play, but there is some and its awesome.I have to go now though so i rushed this but ya BUY THIS GAME! :)Where Dark Souls says ""prepare to die"" Lords of the Fallen says ""prepare to get a lost and go crazy in a labyrinth"" which to me is great because Souls 2 didnt have nearly enough castle gameplay and in Lords you get fully submerged in the depths and dungeons of medievil Cidatels"
