,Recommended,265300,14048176,"Posted: 18 January, 2015",all,SmoothOperator,"Lords of the Fallen is the first ""Souls game"" I ever finished and I do not regret it one bit.It’s a bit more forgiving than the Souls games and perhaps the balance is not as immaculate at different stages of the game, but it makes up for by the share amount of fun it brings to the table and by the much lighter atmosphere is has.The game world has more colours in it, the story telling is more straight forward and level design I found enjoyable although there were a few moments where I briefly felt lost and missed a map.I enjoyed looking for the secret areas in the game, the crafting of weapons, the reward system for not saving.What I wold have liked to see in the game is a little more enemy variety in terms of tactics. Both for the regular baddies and for bosses as half way through the game I found myself just jump-bashing most enemies which got a little repetitive despite being quite fun.The mages provided a little variety (especially spirits) causing me to actually swap weapons but that was basically it.The bosses played out pretty much  similarly as well, just wait for the boss to pull off an attack with the longest cool down and strike him a few times and then retreat (repeat until dead). So little adjustments there would come a long way.The story as such is pretty straight forward with a few alternative endings. I did like the ending but would have liked to see some more meaningful choices in the game and reflections of those choices in the end. But for an action RPG this is fine.In total, I find the low metascores quite unjust. It’s a very fun title with enjoyable gameplay and solid mechanics. The soundtrack is excellent and the graphics are fabulous.In my book, this game is 80/100"
