,Not Recommended,265300,12769803,"Posted: 3 November, 2014",all,Wolverine,"""Three crashes in 5 minutes.""That was my initial review, which was my first one and written in pure frustration due to all the bugs plaguing that game.I will do my best to explain in more details why I would still not recommend this game yet.First of all, I played only the first Dark Souls and I enjoyed it as much as I hated it at the same time. Some of my main issues with Souls was the lack of convenient checkpoint before boss fights - because I am not that hardcore and would like all the help I could get, I would try to summon NPC to help me fight the bosses. Well, I can not remember how much time I got invaded in front of the Dragon Knights duo chamber. The checkpoints are much mroe convenient in Lords - and I can not really think of something done better in that game.The combat feels heavy and clunky - especially when using greatswords/axes. You need so much time to wind up the attack that unless you time it perfectly, you will get staggered by the lightning-fast enemy attack. And you can barely time it properly because of that - the lightning fast enemy attacks. They might be all in heavy armor and with greatshields, but they are attacking so freaking fast and breaking your guard so easy in the begining it is not even funny - nor fair. And you can not break their guard untill late game - it is just not possible. This makes the fight vs some of the shield weilders true nightmare, especially in early game. Even when you learn how to do it, it is still a chore and too time-consuming to be fun. Now I understand they are super-strong demons from other dimension, but for the sake of freaking gameplay - at least make it so we are able to freaking break their guard.Also on the fighting - how can you possibly dual-weild one handed weapon SLOWER and when using it with one hand and shield? Check The Avenger (I think that was the name of the sword), this is ridiculous. Two-hand weilding does not give you speed most of the time, just leaves you more open to attacks. Also - all greatswords have exact the same identical moves - all the greataxes and hammers as well. Actually, most of the weapons are just a reskin with identical move sets. The game suffers heavily from lack of diversity in that department - they should learn from the Souls.Agility weapons, and daggers in particular, feel very bad. They have nice very high damaging combos, but the last part of the combo is usually (with the case of daggers) charging move... which very often miss due ot enemies just slightly moving aside; or you just move past them by your own. Enemies however dont have that problem - if you dodge to the side, they auto-correct their aim and positioning mid-swing and will still hit you. That feels too unfair and cheap, considering they are as already mentioned with unbreakable guard and lightning-fast attacks.The magical system is there just for the sake of having some magic in the game - I played Paladin on my first playthrough and most of the time when I tried to cast anything I would get staggered by the creeps or bosses - because of the abyssmal long casting time, in which your hero stays in one place and makes fancy moves. I would appreaciate if some kind of mobility was invilved like in Souls, where you can still move while casting, but slower. It is ridiculous and not fun at all.The main thing that put me aside from the game and I will not most probably play it anymore is the loot system. Where is the replayability if in your first playthrough you open all the chests and get all the gear?! What if I got some crappy normal version of a very cool sword, and I want to socket it? Forget it - if you want another better vesrion of the sword, you need to know the exact chest and you need to start a new game and to make sure you have good multiplier for higher rarity chance. It would be much more helpful to be able to upgrade the common variation to higher rarity by crafting - or at least have everything drop again on New Game+ and ++ but with higher chance for better rarity.On a side note, I wanted to play agi char. Well, almost midgame and still the best agi-weapon was the one I foung in the very first 30 mins after start. I just gave up at that point.At this point I do not see any reason to play that game again. I was fooled by the pre-release streaming and the nice setting, but I would have never payed £30 for that garbage. The game is too small, too repetitive, too buggy and definetely not worth the price tag.Also keep in mind I have not played after the last patches and although some system issues might have been resolved, I will still not play it because of the all things mentioned above. All of the above is my personal opinion base don my personal experience with this trash, I mean the game, and might differ from yours. I would actually recommend the game after few patches and on a sale for at least 60% off, but not for full price. Do NOT get it for full price, do not make the same mistake as me.If you really bothered to read that - thanks and game on."
