,Recommended,265300,13721550,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Divex82,"If you have the hardware to run this maxed out you are in for a treat. This is one of the best looking multiplatform games out right now. If not, no worries!The gameplay alone is worth playing Lords of the Fallen™. At its core, the game is all about preparation, strategy, and timing one powerful blow or a perfect succession of fast strikes against a vulnerable enemy. It gets tricky when there's multiple foes and little room to work with. That's where this game shines; when your heart races and you're praying you'll make it out alive. If not, that sucks. Just go find your ghost and regain all that precious lost experience points. Die on that one way trip? All is lost!There's a decent story full of lore and interesting characters, monsters, and set-pieces. There's also tons of armor, weapons, and other gear to keep you happy, and the best catch is what loot drops is tied to how much you are willing to wager you won't die. Cash in your experience and the loot multiplier is reset.I love it, and this is from someone who could never really get into the Souls series.P.S. I haven't had one crash or any other issues."
