76561198079606596,Recommended,265300,12804696,"Posted: 5 November, 2014",all,EvilBrainAngelHeart,Game its cool i give it 8/10Just finished it.Crashed 3 times befor i do some changes in my driver options .I hope they will work on sec part and community will help them upgrade those few things what was missing in gameplay.
76561197986609104,Recommended,265300,12812941,"Posted: 5 November, 2014",all,gtox11,"This is a review from someone who loved Darksiders (I had graphical issues with 2, so that was a bummer), loved Kingdoms of Amalur, liked Skyrim but hated the way the third-person was done, and played Dark Souls 2 (on PC) for one hour before getting a refund (my first refund request on Steam in seven years).I bought this game as a filler between Borderlands Pre-Sequel and Dragon Age: Inquisition, but I was horribly wrong in thinking that this game would be just a mediocre filler..Lords of the Fallen is downright amazing.  As most people have said, it plays extremely similar to Dark Souls; however where Dark Souls utterly failed, Lords of the Fallen succeeds in leaps and bounds.Here are my pros and cons:ProsThe controls!  Nothing kills a game for me more than bad controls (which extends to graphical UI as well).  Lords of the Fallen, as I compare it to Dark Souls, has amazing control and ,once you get used to all of the mechanics, gives the player a feeling of personal extension.The challenge!  Okay, I know a lot of people are rolling their eyes.  ""Pfft!  This game is totes easy, noob!""  At times it can be, and then at other times it is pretty brutal.  This is not the typical forgiving game that rewards players just for showing up.  But the real great part is that you, the player, grow with your character.  First you struggle to get a hit in while also blocking and every enemy seems to take 3/4 of your life and your health potions are dwindling.  But a few hours later, that same enemy is swinging at air while you are crushing his head in with ease and losing even 1/10th of your life seems like you just lost focus for a moment.  There is definitely a very rewarding feeling when you grow better as a player instead of just gathering more stat points to win the RNG fight.The variety!  Between strength, agility, and faith weapons, gauntlets, shields, and class spells there is quite a long list of different ways to bash your enemies face in.. and this is without taking into account Runes or Legendary weapon special abilities!  Everything has an optimal use, so there is very little ""useless junk"" lying around.The replayability!  Ever get frustrated that you run out of enemies to kill, or there is no point in starting a new character?  Lords of the Fallen doesn't have that problem.  Enemies respawn everytime you change instances (which actually slows everything down quite a bit), and the classes are varied enough to warrant at least a few playthroughs.The sound effects are good, but for me that is just icing and not really anything that would keep me or stop me from playing.ConsGraphics Optimization.  Now bare with me here.  The graphics are amazing.. truly, and the art style of the armor, weapons, and character models is inspiring.  But I am used to my quaint gtx660 being able to handle most games at either High, Very High, or Ultra depending on the demands.  Lords of the Fallen has me sitting at Medium, and even then I feel the UI lag at times (especially when using spells that have persistent graphical effects).  I can only assume that there has to be some optimization issues there, but it is certainly not written in stone.Once you find your fav weapon, spell, or armor the game can get a little repetitive.  However this is something that happens in all games, and admittedly this game suffers from this problem far less than others.  Definitely a minor issue.That is about all I can think of.  I look forward to a sequel in the future.  For those who are on the fence about buying this one, as long as your money isn't making you choose between this or Dragon Age: Inquisition, then I would definitely place this one very, very high on the list.  Best action RPG I have played since Darksiders 1."
