,Recommended,265300,12689859,"Posted: 29 October, 2014",all,Nuin,"Pretty fun game. If you liked Dark Souls 1 & 2, you'll probably like this one. Doesn't contain as many features as DS2, but has a similar difficulty level (although DS2 bosses are harder). No character creation, which is a minus, but has a reasonable skill/magic level progression.Only 3 classes, so limited replayability. Especially as (apart from the magic) you can essentially play the rogue and the warrior in one play through simply by changing your armour and weapon, if you put some points into agility. This can actually be helpful as versus some bosses you benefit from increased ability to dodge (champion anyone?).The game is hard at first and can be frustrating but once you get used to each type of enemy it's relatively straight forward until you reach a boss, which you then need to figure out.Like DS2, you drop all your experience when you die, but you can retrieve it. However, unlike DS2 the longer it takes you to reach your XP pick-up, the less XP there is when you get there. So the game can be pretty unforgiving, but if you like that then it's good.Visual style is okay I guess, maybe 2 or 3 years out of date but thats alright. The music and sounds are high quality.I've encountered a couple of bugs where if you die by falling sometimes your XP can't be reached. However, there are special items you can use that allow you to get your XP without actually running and getting it (type of potion). I advise never using these unless your XP is bugged as above, as when that happens these potions are the only way to get it back.Other than that, pretty polished game. Recommended."
