76561198013866358,Not Recommended,265300,12734220,"Posted: 1 November, 2014",all,diggsatron,"im going to first say that if you want to buy this game as a bloodbourne warm up (if you have a ps4) then id hold your purchase. when this game works properly it plays well. the problem here is that is crashes far too often and with the check point system this can mean losing all progress made after departing the last crystal. To put it in other words; its like the game crashing is the same as dying in game. if this incredibly frustrating issue ever gets fixed then I can safely say that this is a good somewhat souls style action RPG.gameplay: if you played the souls franchise this game will feel fimiliar if slower. the biggest emphisase in combat is timing, dont get greedy. there is magic in the game but dont expect it to be as varied as dark souls as there are only two types: your starting class spells and a magic gaunlet found later. there are 3 classes each with four spells to level. the class system however only appiles to magic, all other aspects such as equipment and weapons are talored to stats. so i you played a souls game you know what to expect there. most of the enemies in the game are well designed with a few frustrating exeptions depending on what play style your going for. the best fights in the game are the bosses not counting the final (which is a bit of a letdown), which demand cunning and strategy. you feel an emense sense of satifaction when you finally bring one down gaining a special reward after a victory. the only downside is that there are a limited number in the game. as for the common enemies, there are 2 that will quite possibly make you rage quit a few times. one has the ability sap health from you at a range as well as put defence thorns on himself (if you hit him you also hit yourself) and one you need to fing a jar containing an item to pick up or he will constantly regenerate at critical health. if the game balanced these out more it would be a better product but for now they are a head ache. and if your looking for an online aspect, there is none.story: not much to talk about here. the story is presented in a more traditional manor than dark souls but even so it realy only amounst to ""dark god sends demons, kill them and save the world."" the charater you play, that is Harkyn is your typical brooding tough guy with no personality what so ever they might as well had a silent protaginast. there are npc to interact with but they are just as booring. the only reason to progress in the game is to see all the cool armour sets and weapons in the game. there are instaces of player choice but you will often not realy care about the out come of these nor do they realy matter in the end. all in all the story feels phoned in.level design & art: symply amazing, the level design is brilliant in how sprailing and interwoven the world is. as for the art, this is one of the best examples of high gothic dark fantasy I have ever seen. weapons and armour all have this gloriously powerful and embolding look to them like somthing out of warhammer fantasy. the bosses have the look of giants clad in imposing dark armour brandishing fearsome weapons. if the developers put in as much effort into the bug testing of the game i would give this a recomendation.technical: this is where the game has problems. there area far to many minor bugs in regards to the sound and ui to count. there are far to many instances of enemies shooting trough walls or walking out of backstab animations or extreame hit box problems to say this is a must buy. but the one thing that keeps this game so low is the constant crashing. the biggist fear i had while playing this game was not from the towering demons but from the ""lords of the fallen has stoped working"" screen. when this happens, you lose all progress gained from the last check point including looted items. this is unacceptable for a game that wants to be this punishing.Summary: Lords of the fallen is a game that has the potential to but much greater if some key glaring problems are fixed but for now, wait for this game to be patched."
