76561198068867109,Recommended,265300,12729604,"Posted: 1 November, 2014",all,Einax,"GOOD:- The combat feels Dark Souls style, and it's pretty challenging, so if you wanted more Dark Souls, you should try this game.- The story is interesting, though it's not as detailed as the devs promised it to be.- Lots of different weapons and armor, and overall good loot will keep you interested in the game.- It's good for you if you like Darksiders. You'll find lots of similar moods and design decisions in this game.- Graphics are great. It's not Crysis 3, but lights and particle effects look stunning. Character models are also good.BAD:- PC version's optimization is AWFUL. Frequent crashes (especially last few hours of the game), FPS drops on the high-end PCs, and so on.- Camera's behavior is really odd sometimes.- Although Dark Souls style, combat is very slow. You may find yourself annoyed by how slow Harkyn's moves are. Especially his rolls.- Locations often feel repetitive.- Bosses aren't impressive, they're mostly humanoid, and bossfights are not as satisfying as they should be.- Rogue style of playthrough is much more difficult than Warrior.- The game's too short, I've completed it in 13 hours.- Characters' lip-syncing looks incredibly stupid, lips' moves and voices don't match at all.VERDICTI liked the game, and I think it has lots of potential. However, first of all, the devs need to fix the PC version's issues (as I've heard, PS4 version has lots of bugs too) for the game to be playable and enjoyable. I'll be clearly doing a second run as a rogue or warrior after the game is fixed! I'm looking forward to that. As for now, the game is good, but it's not as good as I wanted it to be. And it's definitely not better than Dark Souls or Darksiders.RATING: 68/100. The game is good. Just good, that's it.If you want to read the thoroughly detailed version of this review, please visit:http://alessusreviews.blogspot.com/2014/10/review-1-long-awaited-piece-of-art.html#more"
