76561198062515231,Recommended,265300,19976378,"Posted: 26 December, 2015",all,TAW|Nostradankus,"To give a bit of perspective, I picked up this game - sans DLC - for under 10 bucks, so this clearly influences my opinion of it. Also note that I have played over 300 h of Dark Souls and DSII combined, so whatever I say about the difficulty should be taken with a grain of salt.I liked the game. If you can pick it up a good discount and you need your Souls fix then go for it. That being said, the game has it fair share of issues. I've had a bug where messages telling me a door or chest needed a key would stop appearing about halfway through my playthrough. Damage number also didn't show up any more. Other than that, I had a mostly bug-free experience, eventhough the camera can sometimes be finnicky, especially in tight quarters.On my i7 5th Gen CPU and GTX 780 GPU the game ran smooth pretty much from start to finish. I've had FPS loss some times, but only ever for short periods of time and never below 30.The game looks absolutely gorgeous, both in terms of the art design and the graphics themselves. I loved all the designs, from enemies to armor to the environment. Certain areas can look a bit too similar at times, which leads to a bit of confusion, but overall this game looks - and sounds - very good.Talking about confusing, the layout of the game is very reminiscent of Dark Souls aswell, with a lot of play area in a rather small geographical space. Most areas are interconnected and exploring to find secret passages is a lot of fun.The last point I wanna talk about is the game play itself. I'm not gonna tell you how it's a lot like Dark Souls, you probably already guessed that. I'd rather point out the for me biggest flaw with the gameplay.The player is too slow. Not by much. But just enough to be frustrating in certain places. What I mean by that is that after you attack with most weapons you have a short ""downtime"", a second or so during which you just stand there and can't move or roll away. This by itself is fine, a lot of games have that. But the downtime is just that bit too long, meaning that a lot of the time enemies can punish you for an attack and there is nothing you can do. Their afterswing and stagger just are too short. So with certain enemies winning isnt a matter of being more skilled, it's just a matter of the AI not capitalising on your after swing downtime to combo you to death.On the other hand, I found the later bosses to be fairly easy, almost push overs actually.So, in the end, would I reccommend this game? If you have played Dark Souls and you're waiting for Dark Souls III and need your fix, then pick it up on sale.If you haven't played Dark Souls yet, go play Dark Souls. It's cheaper and aside from the graphics simpily a better game."
