,Recommended,265300,20668523,"Posted: 21 January, 2016",all,Zanfroni,"Lords Of The Fallen (2014):Lords Of The Fallen is developed by CI Games and Deck 13 and it is published by Namco Bandai. This game is an Action RPG pretty much like the ""Souls"" franchise. It has alot of similarities. Inspiration from a great franchise is always good, but is the game itself any good?I'm a huge fan of the ""Souls"" franchise. I played all the way from Demon's Souls to the latest Bloodborne, and I was excited when I've seen the trailer for this game. It looked pretty nice, so I bought the pre-order, hoping to get a great and challenging experience.Now I'll say this right out of the bat, this game looks very nice. The visuals are outstanding, and the art direction is great, although not anything unique. We enter castles, monasteries, demon worlds and shattered places by demonic portals. The gameplay is also great, I was very satisfied. Some people were very disappointed with it, but I had a great time approaching this more realistic style, where every hit felt real.Unfortunately, the game insists in telling a dumb story about redemption. And really, I couldn't give a damn for what was happening. It's not an investing story and you'll end up hating the game if you play it for it's storytelling. The game also features tons of weird glitches and bugs that occasionally happen. There are videos on youtube showing them, but I haven't found any gamebreaking bug. The game was heavily criticized for its optimization and I have to agree. On launch, this game was sometimes unplayable for me, and some people experienced constant crashes and freezes. Never happened to me though.The enemies look nice and are fun to combat, although they can start to get a bit repetitive towards the end. But the challenge is there, and it's nicely implemented. This game is challenging, but never unfair. Unfortunatelly though, I expected a bit more challenge, and that is thanks to some poor level design and some PRETTY bad boss fights. Some of the bosses are extremely fun to play and sometimes masterfully designed and executed, but some others (the second boss, for instance), can make you snooze.The game doesn't have Multiplayer nor any extra mode, but it does have NG+ games, where you replay the entire with the equipment you've been keeping, only the game is harder. It's a quite short experience though, and the DLC (Ancient Labyrinth) is horrible, it's not worth getting (unless on a sale AT LEAST 66%).But overall, I enjoyed playing this game and I think it's quite refreshing to see more games like Lords Of The Fallen and the ""Souls"" franchise.PROS:-Nice challenge-Looks great-Diversity on weapons-Some very fun and challenging bossesCONS:-Some bosses are a joke-Forgettable story and soundtrack-Shorter than you might expect===It's a good challenging game. Buy it on sale if you like games like ""Souls"" or challenging games.===GRADE: B"
