76561197981099982,Recommended,265300,13095233,"Posted: 26 November, 2014",all,SuNin,"I would have to give this a recommend for a few reasons and some accompanying caveats.Combat:  The combat was awesome for me.  This is one of the best aspects of the game.  It really felt that like that good precise Dark Souls style combat.Caveat:  The combat, so long as you were playing a warrior, was great.  I really liked playing as fast rogue like characters, but I had a hard time pulling this off, personally.  The weapon combo system was great, but enemies reacted way to fast to make good use of Rogue type weapons.  I did not however play as a magic user.  I don't usually like that in games like this.Graphics: They are really well done.  The details of the world were really really good.  I also overall like the graphic designs in the game.Caveat: There were some complaints about it being too ""WoW like"".  Big shoulder pads, crazy helmets, a lighter color palette, but these things didn't bother me.  Some of the armors and weapons in this game were truly awesome to see.Sound:  I don't know if this was a bug that was not fixed before I beat the game but:  The enemies often times made sounds from their deaths several seconds after I killed them, it was really strange.  It's a shame too because the creature sounds were good in my opinion.  When they made the sounds they made, it was what I would expect.Replayability:  This is probably the biggest mark against it.  I don't foresee myself going through it again as an alternate class.  I started as rogue type character, then starting going into Strength pretty early on because rogues don't feel viable to me.Other complaints:  Warrior only.  I have said it before but I wanted outline this a bit more.  If you go into a strength build, this allows you to wear the best armors in the game.  You are never much of a damange sponge even with that.  Also, the majority of the time there was simply not enough room to be a character who is flipping all over the place.Another one is that the Shield Bash is the most useful move in the game.  It works against the vast majority of creatures.  It was so useful, I couldn't imagine playing without.  You will come across a lot of guys who are carrying huge shields themselves, and the shield bash is the only thing that I feel works on them.Frustratingly enough, later in the game you will come across enemies that cannot be hurt by physical weapons at all.  At the time I thought I would just have to equip an appropriate rune, but that doesn't hurt them either.  You MUST use your gauntlet.  But if you invested no points in that, then you are looking at a bit of annoyance.  I used a rune that caused my gauntles to catch them on fire, but the effect would end literally when they had barely any perceivable life on their health bar.  I would then dance around avoid their easy to dodge attacks until my magic filled high enough to finish them off.  There are items that help with this, but I don't feel you get enough of them that you can just pop them everytime you need one.  I did finish the game being a bit too over cautious with them though, so that is my fault and not he game.All of this said: I ultimately found my experience enjoyable.  The world was rich and interesting and different enough from any Souls game that it did not feel like a clone at any point.  I would not go back on my decision to buy this at full price, and if you catch it on sale it's an even better buy in my opinion, despite the frustrating parts of the game, which were few and far between."
