,Not Recommended,265300,13260129,"Posted: 6 December, 2014",all,Big Pasta,"My first note is that the game is very short. I beat it in 8 hours of playtime. No multiplayer, limited sidequests that are very vague and confusing levels had me getting mixed up all over the place. There were not very many bosses and they were all pretty easy. Only two bosses actually killed me.This game is NOT Dark Souls. Not even close. It uses dark souls combat mechanics like health potions that refill at checkpoints, dodge rolls, and left hand/right hand on LB/LT and RB/RT. The same mechanics are in it but the feel is much different. Everything in Dark Souls is very thoughtful and you can learn your opponents moves and such to make it a lot easier, but even as a magic build I found myself just smacking everything in the face with my hammer and ignoring damage.It was a very easy game, the only challenging part was that the level layouts are confusing and mazelike. I did enjoy the game, but it felt like it could have been so much more. I will probably do the NG+ but I don't recommend it for $50. Get it on sale and it will be fun for a while.TL:DR Fun but too short and no multiplayer. Do not expect it to be like Dark Souls. Mechanics are similar, but the game is way different."
,Recommended,265300,13801833,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,mLatchi,I know how people say its Darksider 2 for the cheap and are scepticle about this game but im here to give my first thoughts and personal opinion on this game. Lords of the Fallen is a very unique game even though it carries many of dakrsiders qualities. DarkSiders 2 is more of a death simulator and This game is somewhat a hack and slash. I mean its not entirely lets rush in and spam left mouse but it is a lot more of you being involved and attacking rather then waiting and watching your enemies attack patterns. Even though its more hack and slash like its not more forgiving. When you die you leave the white mist like object behind you and it gives you a certain amount of time to grab it. It starts from 100% and works its way down. Even though this seems easy the fact that the enemy will still be there makes you think if you would rather fetch it or attempt to kill the enemy first. Many people said it was a pushover but for me this was not the case since i didnt play darksouls or darksouls 2 before this game. Think of it as a kind of tutorial game for people who havent played Darksouls. Since i have spoken about my personal experience i will now tell you about graphics gameplay and issues. At this moment in time even though i have played 2.4 hours i have not had one single issue with this game. It has ran smoothly except for the second boss where it dropped fps for about 1 second. Graphic wise this game is beautiful. The beautiful environment and the way everything works with one another can change it from being peacful to a bloodbath in an instant without feeling clunky and all over the place. The voice used for the main character suits him but he lacks in personality which makes it quite difficult to fall in love with the characters so you feel connected. I rate it 8-10 and if anyone needs a game reviewed that i have add me and ill write you one
