,Recommended,265300,12732402,"Posted: 1 November, 2014",all,TheSlimReaper,"Lords of The Fallen is Action RPG isnpired off the Dark Souls Series, as so it seams. Lords of the Fallen takes certain aspects from Dark Souls that made it great, puts it into Lords of the Fallen, flips it on its side, and attemtps to make it better but in a different way. They succeed in some aspects and fails in others, however, Lords of the Fallen is a fun experience and should not be missed if a sale comes by your way.PROS:Great combat, feels slow at first but after an hour or two it feels more naturalParrying that feels satisfactoryHard but rewarding bossfightsVery Unique armor sets and rewardsThe player gets rewarded for taking risks with the games unique risk and reward systemCONS:When preforming a backstab animation or parry, the camera will change to an awkward position.Some boss fights may have difficult movesets, but some fights are only difficult because of an INSANE healthbarCRASHES occur no matter if you have a amazing pc or not. ( I have crashed a decent amount and I have a powerful PC.The game is not very well optimized which lead to the crashes.Lots of random glitches and bugs that just make the game feel unpolished.The level design left me wanting more, instead I just kept revisitng the same areas.There are several enemies in the game that are invincible all the time and they suck, until you find a way to make them vulnurable which is possible for all those type of enemies, except for one in particular. The one you can never kill ( at least I couldn't and I did almost everything optional) is very very agrivating, especially in small halways.Verdict:Lords of the Fallen in the end is a well made game. It did not fail and is not perfect However, it suprised the gaming community with a difficult, rewarding, yet a fresh new experience that is one of the first games to take inspiration off the Souls genere and succeed. If you have the spare cash to pick up Lords of the Fallen, do so, but preferabley at a reduced price in my humble opinion.Rating : 8"
