76561198005547355,Recommended,265300,20277412,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,AskMeAboutJesus,"This game is an amazing Rune....Almost no game is completely perfect.  This game is not perfect by any means of the imagination.  However, this game has some amazing maps, monsters and difficult challenges.Pros - The graphics are super sweet!!  I played this at 2560x1440p with a G-sync IPS  monitor and averaged between 80-100 FPS most the game.  The game looks fantastic- The monsters in this game are really fun to fight (not to mention they have cool names).  You fight people like the Beast, Champion, Annhialater, Worshipper, Guardian, etc... and they range in difficulties, but are all fun to fight!- The controls are good.  Some people complain that sometimes you hit someone and it doesn't register.  This is true, but it doesn't happen very often.- The loot system is nice because you can carry endless amounts of items.  However, you still have to be careful how much you are actively carying, because this will cause you to become overcumbered.- Once you beat the game, you restart and can select a different area of magic and you keep your XP and weapons, abilities, spells, etc.. and play again.  This time the monsters are really difficult and it really feels like you are starting over!- It's not Dark Souls- Got this on sale for $9.99 (worth every penny)Cons - When I first started playing this game, it crashed on me a few times.  When it crashed, I lost an hours worth of saved XP and almost rage quit the game completely.  After the first few stages, it never crashed again!- In two of the portal (challenge areas) areas, I immediatley died when going in there and my XP simply vanished!  I was so upset, that I found a youtube video to farm experience to get my XP back.  Take that game!!! - Lesson learned, be careful when going into the portal challenge areas!- Voice acting is laughable.  The story isn't very good either, but you will meet fun people along the way that help you stay engaged throughout the story.- Not really a con, but sometimes you will get stuck trying to find an objective and you will run around for long times trying to find out where to go next.Summary - Buy this game if you want to have an awesome experience in an open world RPG.  Yes it does have its own issues, but if you like Dark Souls, then you will like this game.  It's great!  I'm really hoping they make a Lords of the Fallen 2!!!!"
