,Not Recommended,265300,12801319,"Posted: 5 November, 2014",all,Val,"Short summary: A linear dark souls style RPG with a more direct narrative but glaring issues in combat balance, general stability & performance and unfair AI.In depth:Combat felt unfair despite being told enemies follow the same rules as the player, it did not feel like that in any shape or form. At times it'd be laughably easy circle strafing enemies to backstab them and other times enemies would treat your shield as if it were made of paper because you went the wrong way.Finding where to go boils down to trial and error, did that enemy kill you in 2 hits? Try somewhere else in this bland landscape to explore, it's difficult to get your bearings when so much of the environment looks the same.Performance wise I am running the game with 2 Nvidia GTX760's on SLI and am seldom seeing the framerate go over 40, it sticks in the 30-35 range for most of the time. Animations on enemies looking very jarring at times, stuttering as they moved in combat with me, taking me out of the experience entirely.side note:A potential fix for Nvidia users is to switch physx control over to CPU instead of your GPU, doing this got me an extra 10fps though your mileage may vary.Addition:I gave the game another chance and shortly after the 3rd boss and its convuluted tactics I encountered an enemy that used a grab attack on me, which then caused my character to fall through the floor of the game and land into a room below of which there was no way out as the door could only be opened from the other side. I had no choice but to quit the game, losing my progress.In closing this looks and feels like a Dark souls clone trying to jump on the bandwagon before it even got rolling. With the horrible issues in combat, exploration, bugs/glitches and optimisation, I would not recommend playing it at all in this state."
