76561198038157545,Not Recommended,265300,16458523,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Hank Hill,"I played this game at a friends house on the console, and when the Steam Summer Sale started I picked this up at what I would consider a somewhat good deal. However, everything didn't go to plan and I ended up refunding the game pretty quickly, my short rundown...The Good: For one, this game looks beautiful. One of the prettiest games I've ever seen, and the artistic style of the world, its inhabitants, and the gear are great. The performance was  also really good given the amount of visuals the game pushes. The gameplay itself (which strongly resembles the Demon/Dark Souls style) was also fun, with its own quirks compared to other games out there. I actually liked the leveling system for a game like this, and the interface (although not the most keyboard friendly) was really helpful telling me what I needed.The Bad: As of June 16th, the day this was written, I just couldn't get over the crashes from this game. What's worse, when you crash you'll be left off the last save crystal you used. When a feature of the game is NOT to use them to build up a monster  multiplier for the equivalent of bonus XP, a crash is devastating. In addition, I noticed a ton of odd audio anomalies with the game. Voices were never a consistant volume, and it didn't seem audio positioning was done very well either. The voice acting of the game was...not so great, and the lip sync wasn't that great either. Your character's attitude seems a bit silly at times, and overall the story was a bit hit and miss.I really want to like this game, and if it didn't have so many problems I think it could've been a really fun game. But my time in game was spent redoing everything I had just done due to crashes, coupled with the fact that the game didn't really seem to entice me to push the story forward, something the Souls series does fantastically.At this time, I can't give a solid recommendation for the game, but it's definitely on my list of games to revisit in the future, because it seems like this could have good potential."
