76561197971877162,Recommended,265300,12731672,"Posted: 1 November, 2014",all,Asses of Fire,"I feel like I can safely review this after just a few hours.  If you've ever played any of the Souls games then you'll get the combat system right away.  I didn't even need the tutorial and the keybinds for a controller are literally the same as Souls with a few minor exceptions due to spells.If you enjoyed the combat system of the Souls games then you'll enjoy Lords.  If you are coming here looking for an epic story then turn around...the story is the weakest part of the game.  It doesn't give you that feeling of dread like the Souls games do.Graphics are outstanding, as are the combat animations.  You can safely run this game at 30 fps on high settings with a last gen video card (i.e. nvidia gtx 660 minimum).Difficulty is something to be desired.  I cleared 2 major bosses without breaking a sweat or dying once.  I still have not died after a few hours of gameplay.  The game is a tad difficult in the first hour but quickly gets easier as you pump points into stamina so you can swing that sword like 20 times and the monster doesn't have a chance.As for the price...well here is where I disagree.  Its a full priced AAA game that has no multiplayer mode.  So what will happen is you'll spend 15-20 hrs completing the campaign then just do it again on the same toon to level up all your stats; fans of the souls series will know what I'm referring to here.   If you can, wait until a steam sale when its half off, then it'll be worth your time.  I still reccomend it right now though if you're a fan of action rpg's and you have some throw away cash."
