,Recommended,265300,13834828,"Posted: 4 January, 2015",all,Thera,"First, in just a couple of words, I recommend this, but you should know what you're getting into.The developers clearly intended this as an homage to the Dark Souls franchise, and after playing through and beating the game once, that is being charitable.  Homage or ""whole sale theft,"" you be the judge.  But for purposes of whether you should play it, it matters only insofar as you go in looking for an exact replica of Dark Souls' brutal challenge and unforgiving combat.  Despite many shared features/mechanics, Darks Souls this is not.  This is Guy Fieri to Dark Souls' Gordon Ramsay.  And you know what?  Sometimes you just want a Honky-Tonky Double Barrel Meat Loaded Blast (with extra Jack Daniels Sauce!) instead of caviar.  And that's OK.If you can approach this game as the testosterone, Monster energy drink fueled Todd McFarlane 90's nightmare (knightmare, I think Todd would have gone with) that it is, you'll have a blast.  I swear they read every Spawn comic ever and just lifted art and designs from it.   It has much of the following: KNIFE ARMOR!, KNIFE HANDS!, KNIVES THAT HAVE/ SHOOT MORE KNIVES!, BIG ABSURD COMPLETELY UNFUNCTIONAL F*CKING WEAPONS!, BROODING!, GRRRRRR!Combat mechanics are decent once you get the hang of them.  I used an agility Cleric build (WITH DOUBLE F*CKING KNIVES), so I was pretty much untouchable after I learned to time my rolls and figure out how to dance away from things then dart in to slice and dice.  Magic gets pretty broken across the board, I read.  I used the support path and ""Shelter"" immediately breaks the game if you focus on spamming it before, during, and after fights, as it can completely replentish your health bar.  I used it when I needed it, instead of as a security blanket, because the combat was pretty fun and not white-knuckle insane like DS (which can, again, be a good thing!)  I died a fair amount of times, usually through carelessness or camera issues, but I never felt totally SOL after getting killed after a decent amount of progress since the last checkpoint, again unlike DS.Bosses are great looking (as is the entire game if GOTHIC HELLSCAPES RAAARGH! are your thing), and pretty straightforward.  I did not have to rely on cheesing/kiting any of them.  The first few boss fights, before you figure out how to dominate, can be intense.As far as the story and character devel....HAHAHA just kidding.  Here, have some wicked knife armor and go kill some big f*cking monsters.7/10 will probably check out NG+."
