76561197994360800,Recommended,265300,13844026,"Posted: 4 January, 2015",all,AJ Rockwell,"As a huge fan of Souls series, I've been waiting for some time to get my hands on this game. But due to some negative reviews stating the game's bugginess I have waited for a sale. And so I got this 40% off on Christmas Sale. Straight up I honestly think this game is not worth 50€, so I recommend waiting for a sale if you want to play it.The pros: This game looks like a third-person Diablo (and I love that art style) with somewhat clumsy combat compared to Souls - but that is a fresh addition I welcome. Thanks to that there is some replay value (choose a different offensive, magic, etc.). When you get yourself over the bugs or FPS issues, the gameplay is like a breeze. The more you kill the more XP you get and this has kept me engaged. Finding new, imba weapons and armor that both look gorgeous always makes you happy.The Meh: The boss encounters miss their ""wow"" factor (almost always a huge guy with a huge weapon) and they all can be straight up zerged - the only tactic is wait for them to be dazed after they swing their weapon and strike. The voice acting ranges from average to bad to poor along with lipsync. The story is bland and uninteresting. The crafting system could have used more love and invention. Oh and that backtracking sometimes gets on your nerves if you have poor spatial orientation combned with the maze-like design. NG+ is 0 challenge but at least you get the feeling of revenge on the poor sods that gave you hard times.The cons: The few initial hours of gameplay were ridden with bugs, huge framerate drops (this game is very poorly optimized and I hope a patch will fix that soon) but since setting the details to medium-low with all facy stuff off I got it to run somewhat acceptable on my GTX660.Final words: Enjoy the game for what it is - its combat and you looking badass, hurling enemies around with your huge weapon, and get it on sale for ~16 hours of gameplay."
