76561198005919137,Not Recommended,265300,19210554,"Posted: 22 November, 2015",all,Provoker,"Some dark forces invade, again. Some guy is released from prison to fight the aforementioned dark forces, again. We don't know what exactly is happening, again. We have to fight an kill every one, again. We die, the sector is repopulated and we try to kill everyone, again. You probably see where I'm getting at, the game is a pretty and somewhat polished collection of clichés  with an emphasis on 1 on 1 (maximum 1 on 3) sword/axe/hammer/etc fight and some magic.The game is similar to the Dark Souls series, with an emphasis on combat and loss of experience in case if you die (no quick saves here). It is a nice action RPG based in a citadel and *drum roll* dimension of the evil invaders. The game will also take some time to get used to controls and some glitches.Pros:•	Sometimes interesting battles•	Reflexes are important•	Audio/video quality of the game is 9/9•	some battle realismCons:•	somewhat glitchy controls and camera•	no map (yep, you have to memorise the locations)•	battles become systematic once you learn the enemy types•	boss fight are often frustrating because of controls, and become easy once you figure out bosses' fight patternAll in all this is a solid mid-tier action RPG, it is not worth the full price, so I can only recommend it for $20-25 if you have 12-20 hours to kill.One Grumpy Russian score: 6 out of 10 - not as tempting as vodka, but an a nice alternative when you have none and have no mood for Dark Souls.For more reviews join:http://steamcommunity.com/groups/ogrreview/"
