,Recommended,265300,12756802,"Posted: 2 November, 2014",all,Katalist X,"If you are a fan of dark/demons souls then you might enjoy this game. Visually appealing with a gothic theme. The combat is slower than that of the Souls series', however, it is enjoyable. In some aspects the atmosphere is better than in the souls games. The armor and weapon design is artistic, definetely not bland or simple for most. The sound design and voice acting is quite good and plays a very large part in setting the tone of the game and it's environments. The spells are interesting, but lacking. When you pick a spell class (ie mage rogue or warrior) you are stuck with those spells and cannot get the others, I could be mistaken, but I havent been able to do this. The upgrade system through the use of runes is pretty basic. No fast travel capabilities despite having many instances in the game where you are tasked to backtrack a long distance to a previous area.Overall this game is pretty good and is worth a buy in my opinion."
