e novelty of this combination does wear after repetitive encounters (there are a few reused bosses to normal mobs). It's actually disappointing that it does not go anywhere. The last enemies you fight you fight the same way as the first you fought.Basically most of your fun will be early during first playthrough which is not that much content for the money. The story is straight forward and linear which can be both a pro and con but the reality is you have one real choice in the game; everythinge else is an illusion of choice and does not matter making you sorta wonder if the game would be better without these extras... Like yetka, she could be cut and nothing would change... negatively atleast..."
