76561197998048996,Recommended,265300,12733036,"Posted: 1 November, 2014",all,Wind,"A decent game that stands on its own.Some principles of the game are taken from the Dark Souls: dual wielding and shield mechanics, stamina bar, equipment weight effect on speed, limited health potions, respawning enemies, checkpoints, necessity for tactical combat, backstabing and a game world that does not care if you live or die. But if you try to play it like Dark Souls, you will likely fail miserably. The enemies are different and combat strategies necessary to beat those enemies are different too. The RPG aspect of this game is much more clearer than that of Dark Souls. The combat for the most part is enjoyable - your character really feels like a decent warior who, while he must pay respect to what the enemy does, can stand his own.Oh and one piece of advice. Stock on the fire resistance shards..."
