76561198053129007,Recommended,265300,12674302,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,MaJoNesbø,"In case you haven't read other reviews: the game seems to crash a lot, though I'm fortunate to not have that problem. So be aware if you're going to buy.Otherwise, as a Dark Souls fan, I really like this game. So far I've only played as a rogue, and it's quite the challenge. I have to approach each encounter with caution and figure out what kind of tactics work against which enemies. It feels almost more tactical than Dark Souls, though not as difficult. As a rogue I find myself using parries, backstabs and combos more than I propably would as a more heavy hitting class. Every swing of the dagger counts and every dodge must be thought through.The bosses I've fought so far are enjoyable to fight, but not really that hard once you figure out how to avoid their attacks and when to attack. By the way, dodging into overheads in this game is a baaaaad idea, I died a couple of times because I was used to doing it in Dark Souls.Overall the gameplay is great, I don't really care about the artstyle, story etc., gameplay is the reason I got this game. A lot of Souls fans seem to view this game as some sort of threat to the Souls games, personally I'm just happy to see more games adopt the Souls combat system.A lot of people will hate this game because it either is too similar to Souls or too dissimilar to Souls. But if you're a Souls fan and think you'll enjoy this game, chances are great that you will. If you haven't played the Souls games yet, this could very well be the gateway drug for you."
