76561198044291624,Not Recommended,265300,12850785,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,Bass God,"I really wanted to like this game. I loved Dark Souls and so anything close to that style of game can easily pique my interest. Unfortunately I just found way too many unsavory aspects to this game to  be able to continue playing. This game's entire concept is fighting. Attack combos, countering, parries, etc. I found that the combat in this game however was largely lackluster. Everything must be fair. If you die your reaction shouldn't be ""WTF, thats stupid."" it should be more like ""Damn, I was impatient and didn't block when I should have."" You don't want to feel robbed every time you die. The majority of my deaths seemed to be the former. Some monsters just don't seem to have been optimally programmed. One monster in particular is one of the first monsters you will encounter. I'm not sure if it's intended to be a parry or what but he will hit you with his shield and immediately (looks glitchy) hit with his sword doing 100% hp. I honestly don't believe that was intended but this just one example of some of the awkward combat situations in this game. The timing window for weapon combos/parries are just too difficult to pull off (maybe it's just some weapons). The easiest of enemies will gip you out of a fight. Playing this game made me appreciate Dark Souls on a whole new level. Realizing that the timing of the enemy attacks along with your own were nearly perfect. TL;DR the combat in this game can be down right enfuriating. Most enemies get the jump on you, giving you even more of a disadvantage. Not to mention text typos, floating combat damage text that have a valid reason. This game isn't worth more than 15 dollars (I feel robbed). Even if it were $15 it wouldn't be worth the time playing it. It's too bad because some of the ideas were seemingly interesting and if done right would have made for intruiging character development but with gimpy combat it all goes out the window. Best case scenario, they have a major fix to all these bugs but that isn't going to happen. Best idea is to just move on."
