,Recommended,265300,13176843,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,Kazaf,"To all those that kept crashing: Try going into the game option in steam and clear your cache, that's what stopped the crashing for me :)Now for the actual quick review (once the crashing stops, and played with a gamepad, which is a must for this game IMO) Using the following machine spec:i7 4820k16GB ramGTX770 x 2 SLIThis grants me 55~60fps indoor and around 45~60fps outdoor (vsync enabled)Pros:- Incredible character/armor/weapon/map graphic designs: Absolutely LOVE the styles, it is exactly what I wanted in a dark fantasy RPG game. The map textures are gorgeous and the weapons and armors all ""feels"" heavy and powerful, which brings me to the second point- Combat: The delay between pressing the attack button to the point of impact varies between weapon, giving it a much greater sense of realism and challenge, since you do have to time all your attacks and it varies from weapon to weapon. Along with the vibration from the gamepad, it really does make you feel like a freaking beast every time you smash that warhammer into the monsters' skulls. Although some find this to have slowed the combat down, personally I think it’s great since it’s something different to all the other combat games out there.- Level design: Now I know some people didn't like the maps because they think the areas didn't look ""different"" enough and the map is too confusing, but in honesty i think that was the point of it. This place is meant to look like a gigantic gothic maze that u might get lost in. The differences are distinct enough that u can tell the difference but subtle enough that u feel like everything is connected, i personally very much enjoyed the challenge it presents.- LOVE the varieties in weapon, not only do they look fantastic, but there's also a lot of it! As with all action RPG character building games, the loots are always what keep the game interesting. Could do with more armor sets though i think.Cons:- Lack of range weapon variety - you are stuck with the gauntlet that u picked up from the get-go, even though u can change the projectile type by switching out runes, is still a little annoying. Especially when comparing to the melee variety- The storyline is rather uninspiring. Definitely could do with better dialog options, and preferably more consequences depending on your action so u feel like u are actually making an impact to the game- Boss combat is too easy. When it comes to these kind of games, i fully expect to die at least 3~4 times in every boss fight, ripping my hair out, then finally getting the satisfaction of finally figuring out how to beat that ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ down. Not really getting it here as the boss fights are rather easy.- Game is a little too short (I'm not done yet but I’m getting close i think), if they somehow manage to double the game length then it'll be absolutely perfectAll in all, as a fan of the DS series, I think this is an excellent game that was heavily inspired by its predecessor and did a great job doing it. If the game didn't crash so often like it does for many, I think the reviews would've been much, much more positive. I'm personally having an absolute blast smashing mobs with my warhammer while admiring how awesome my character looks, going to look forward to the DLC and hopefully (fingers crossed) a sequel to this fantastic game (without the crash bug this time)."
