,Recommended,265300,12671269,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,*FPCG| LeviathaN,"..::This review will be changed from time to time until I finish the game::..Trailer visuals are slightly better than the game itself, but whatever, the game still look awesome.Game mechanics are a little... distinct. I think the more you battle without dying or saving, the more/best rewards you get as the game progresses. If you die, you lose all the points I guess, but you have the option to store then so you won't lose then, but won't receive better loot.Sounds are ok, calm soundtrack, boss battles with slightly accelerated songs.The game style (not the visual) remember Dark Souls.P.S.: I died before I can land a single hit on the first enemy, but now I'm used to battle :PSo:Story: Can't say so far.Graphics: 10/10. Really detailed.Visuals: ?/10. Can't really say, I'm still on the castle. so I don't know about the outside world visuals yet.Music/Soundtrack: 8/10. Fine. Could be a little better.Combat Mechanics: 9/10. Yep, very simple. The more heavier you are, more slow your attacks, but more hits you can take. Some games just ignore this.Skills: X/10. I don't know how to properly use then yet, but I think they're ok."
76561197979689489,Recommended,265300,12676146,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,AwesomeViking,"What do i think about it? Hmmmmm. As a Veteran in the Demon/Dark Souls series i find this game rather entertaining. There is no extreme difficulty (atleast not on the first playthrough), although the game is hard, just not Dark Souls hard. I would look at it more like a harder, 3rd person Diablo 2/3, and that is what really hooked me. The awesome gear, the leveling system.I advice you to not head into this game, thinking you are getting a Dark Souls experience! If that is what you want, go play DS1 or DS2. If you want a decent hard, entertaining, hammer your foes styled game, then this is what you should play!"
