76561198011515629,Not Recommended,265300,12734695,"Posted: 1 November, 2014",all,Blackcompany,"A beautiful game with gorgeous environments that tries - and utterly fails - to be Dark Souls. Weapons swing too slowly by far, and enemies recover from strikes - both their own and staggers - far too quickly. Environments are crowded and character models are far too large for said environs. Bosses are larger enemies with enormous health bars and quick recovery from animations.All in all, its more exercise in frustration, than challenge. I recommend most fans - and especially those who came for more tight Souls like game play - avoid this title. Hopefully many of the weapon speed and animation recovery issues will be fixed in a patch, but barring that, skip this and go back to Dark Souls or its sequel, as both are far superior to this blatant clone."
