,Not Recommended,265300,32179751,Posted: 4 June,all,toconnell,"There is a school of criticism that holds limited experience of a thing as disqualifying: if you don't have a full appreciation of a thing, your opinion is necesarily incomplete, partially-formed, less useful, etc.Having spent a little less than an hour with Lords of the Fallen, what I have to say about it is without a doubt based on a very incomplete consideration, so make what you will of it.Between its phoned-in, me-too character and environment designs (which make the second-rate, copy-cat toss-offs of Darksiders look downright creative by comparison) and the fact that it shamlessly and half-assedly apes all of the worst parts of Dark Souls gameplay/control design apparently without realizing what makes DaS fun in the first place, Lords of the Fallen is a complete non-starter.One could certainly make the argument that my opinion is superficial and, if I had stuck with Lords of the Fallen, I might have found something redeeming about it, but to that I can only say that I have but one life to live, and I have neither the time nor the inclination to embark upon an 80-plus-hour search for some kernel of fun in this mercilessly unoriginal, punishingly cheap-feeling Souls-like/Souls-clone simply to justify my opinion that Lords of the Fallen is an absolutely irredeemable piece of trash.If you managed to stick with it and you found something you like in this game, good on you.Me? I refuse to do it."
