,Not Recommended,265300,12674980,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,4th,"I wish I hadn't expected this but I did. This game is an overhyped Dark Souls clone that isn't sure if it wants to be a casual game or a difficult one.I see a lot of people complaining about the boses being hard, but the actual difficulty of these bosses doesn't come from the mechanics of the bosses themselves, but rather from the lack of damage they receive and the amount of damage they deal. I'd prefer a boss that is mechanically challenging rather than a punching bag that takes lots of hits to kill. The second boss actually stands there shielding himself while you fight off AI's because the devs were too lazy to think of an interesting mechanic.The graphics of the game are beautiful, but I feel like nobody plays a Dark Souls style game for the graphics. We play it for the challenge and this game does not deliver on that. It isn't hard, in fact I only died once and that was after the third ""bonfire"" without using a single potion or healing. If you get damaged it is because a mob was hidden cheekliy around a corner, or because a mob has a super quick ability that isn't possible to predict.One of the biggest gripes I have with the game is the ability combos do not seem to be well thought out. Often you will be found knocking an enemy back with the first swing, only to have the second swing not even reach them once they've been knocked down which gives the game the feeling that it hasn't been tested fully.Another thing I've noticed about the game is the glitches, the second boss freezes his animation sometimes and you think he's vulerable but he is still moving underneath and can smack you in the face while you go to swing at him. A game based on beating bosses and progressing should not have these issues.On top of these faults, there is the crashing. I was half way through the second boss and the game suddenly crashed. All of the other people saying that crashing is a big problem are correct. Before anyone asks I use a 780 and my specs are well suited for this game. The game has crashed 4 times for me so far.edit: Since writing the above, I've played another few hours and had another 6 crashes. I'm officially finished with this game until they fix this crashing issue. I've set all graphics to minimum and it is still doing it. Here's a screenshot:http://i.imgur.com/oa7QTzE.jpgI would give this game about a 6/10 overall. The main positive points are the aesthetic level design, graphics and appealing armour sets. Negative things are the attack combos, long levels that don't flow well together. Also, bosses feel like they are just big meat sacks rather than the player being able to mechanically outplay them."
