76561198126001349,Not Recommended,265300,12682997,"Posted: 29 October, 2014",all,toughnuts15,"I'm a huge fan of Demon's Souls and Dark Souls 1/2... replaying is never an issue because I have equal amounts of fun with new builds, challenge runs, speedrunning, cosplaying, pvp, etc.  The souls games fill whatever void you want them to, because they are designed and balanced with an expert touch, and they are deep on many levels.LotF should not be compared to the Souls series.  It has somewhat similar gameplay concepts, but the execution is so different that it's almost not worth comparing.  Combat is slow (even with the rouge character), and it's just simply not balanced.  Heavy armor and strength seems to be easy mode while going light doesn't carry enough of an advantage to be worthwhile.  It's nearly impossible to avoid all damage, and that seems to be part of the game... trade hits then use a potion.On the subject of weapons/shields... I hate that there's no flexibility in weapon combinations.  I want to be able to swap between a heavy shield and buckler quickly mid-battle for a parry... I don't want to: hit select, point my left stick to 4:00, hit A, find the other shield in the menu, select it, hit B a couple times to cancel out.  Then... what was I doing again? Oh yeah... I was gonna parry.  Enemy dead... lets switch back to my heavy shield (uh!).  If you like to play with the same sword and shield all the time, this is not a problem, but what a difference to the souls series!Finally, and most importantly, the game crashes and glitches constantly.  I think it crashed 3 times in the first 45 minutes of play, and I came across some other strange glitches where enemies would freeze for a minute and then do things they were not meant to.  I expect this stuff to get resolved in patches, but it's not a good start.All in all, it might be fine when you want a short diversion, but it's not something to get excited about."
