,Not Recommended,265300,12672965,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,DFCHarem,"Do not buy this game yet as the devs latest patch has yet to fix the stability of the game. I am sure it is fun and all but when the game crashes over and over again before being able to experience what the game has to offer is very hard to accomplish. Not recommending due to the fact some people may not even be able to play the game with the required specs due to the devs not debugging and properly testing the game on pc for these types of things.UPDATE #1: Finally managed to get the game to not crash that often(still crashes once per 20 minutes if lucky otherwise 5-10 minute intervals....) but the performance and fps tends to drop and slow down to 1-2 fps. This normally happens though loading into a new zone and on some enemies/bosses who have a lot of effects and what not.Ignoring the technical side though the game is enjoyable and I am sure much more enjoyable if I did not go a Faith build as 9 hours in and I have found only 4 Faith weapons and at least 25+ of STR and AGIL weapons. This lack in variety is somewhat upsetting but still if you play the other builds you will have plenty of options to pick from. Same goes for the armor it all looks over the top and wide variety to choose from and mix and match.The combat unless using daggers or duel weilding swords is very sluggish. At the start of the game the slow speed is fine but when enemies can combo later on and poise break in 2 hits swinging at the speed of molasses is not fun and you feel like you have not progressed at all while the enemies have. Many of the bosses are interesting and have their own mechanics but some are meh while other fights will stick with you. Overall the combat is fine but not much more for me than that. Though I do enjoy it even though it can be frustrating at times when thinking back to souls games and how fluid the combat was. Here it is much slower for non duel weild or 1h weapons.Now my biggest problem besides performance is lack of enemy types and the map. The variety in enemies is very limited and you will be seeing the same ones over and over again. Same goes for the scenery and zones. At first it will seem big and lots to explore but once you get used to the game you will notice that it is very linear, which I don't hold against it, but the game forces you to backtrack over and over with minor variations to enemy spawns. There are only 2 areas the real world and the other dimension which both are not that large but have many intertwining passages and corridors. Since most of the terrain in these areas look a like I found myself wasting time trying to figure out where I was and needed to go. I am not this bad at having a sense of direction in games but I found myself lost numerous times walking in circles.Overall I still don't recomend to buy the game as is due to the game still having performance issues and the fact that the content of the game is not as vast as it makes out to be. Though if you are a fan soul like games then this is a safe buy since I trust the devs will get the bugs sorted out eventually but for those who are not fans but may want to try out the game I say wait a little and get on sale or at a later date when the bugs are squashed.I say the game is a solid 7/10. It will keep you entertained but has its flaws stopping it from being more than just another above average game."
