76561198055463150,Not Recommended,265300,18192778,"Posted: 25 September, 2015",all,Knight Life,"Seeing how one of the selling points of the game was ""how it's like Dark Souls"" I'll be making plenty of comparisons with it, just a heads up.First of all let's take a look at the combat. The combat is designed in a way that forces you to take certain combat styles that you would prefer not to, such as the use of magic to defeat certain opponents that are practically invulnerable to physical damage, so essentially limiting your freedom of choice.Though the game has a reasonable number of weapons most of these weapons aren't really viable choices since many if not all enemies will not even be slightly staggered by the impact of these weapons and since they are often faster than you can dodge, you're going to get hit. And not just one hit, these are usually at least three consecutive hits in a row while you're stun-locked. Some enemies drain your stamina while they're hitting you effectively preventing you from either blocking or dodging after their sequence of attacks, making it easy for them to do it again until you're dead.Most enemies have near-perfect tracking, meaning that rolling away from an attack might make the first of the three-attack combo miss while the other two will still hit.Another problem that I somewhat talked about is the speed of some attacks. Some attacks of enemies are practically instantaneous and seeing how your character is slower than a cryogenically frozen snail, you're not going to block unless you already had your shield up, nor are you going to quickly counterattack it or dodge it.Another design flaw is that some enemies are just given everything for no apparent reason; explode on death, poison attacks, fire attacks, fast grapple attack that will eat away half your health and then finish you off while your character is recovering on the ground.In short, lots of artificial difficulty resulting in a game that punishes you for things that are often unavoidable.Edit:- Additionally the game blatantly reuses models of old armors and weapons.-Every now and then you'll see your weapon visually hit an enemy without actually damaging them at all-Some enemies are able to interrupt certain attack animations to instead use one of their much faster attacks, making it fairly useless to see what an enemy is doing since a proper response to the first attack animation will still have you get hit by the second attack-Walking into human corpses makes them grunt in pain. What."
