76561198018485648,Recommended,265300,20269277,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,pjcrosby,"Writing a review for this game is difficult as while it is enjoyable its also fairly frustrating. As someone that has played Dark Souls 2 for hundreds of hours, I can see how this game can be compared to that game on the surface. This game allows you to lock on enemies and circle them like in souls and also requires you to understand the attack patterns of the enemies to determine how to beat them. Having said that this game is really quite a different experience from Souls. While the non-boss enemies are almost too easy with simple attack patters, the boss enemies can be ridiculously difficult if you don't have the correct stats/weapons/armor set up for that boss. Rather than skill, beating the bosses really just requires knowledge of a particularl character configuration suited to defeat the boss. While some bosses took me 20 plus attempts to beat, I mostly felt frustrated rather than satisfied when I finally beat them. Its a fun game to get on sale, but don't expect the satisfaction of a Souls game where any particular configuration can defeat the enemies if you are skilled enough."
