,Recommended,265300,12692985,"Posted: 30 October, 2014",all,Yiasmat,"(09/10) - Near PerfectionI had no real expectations or hopes for this game. I bought it as it looked nice and i wanted to try the ""dark souls copy"" like everyone else said it was.But as i played it, there is no way of describing it better than this:This so called ""clone"" of dark souls surpasses it in every way i know.- The graphics look waaaay better, giving the game a better feeling of the ambiente and the environment.- The combat system is actually copied 1:1 from dark souls. Every button does the same, but as it adds different movesets, more interesting spells, gauntlets and more weight classes, it is deeper than the system in dark souls itself.- The bosses are absolutly amazing. Not only have they different stages and change their appearance accordingly, they also all require you to switch the way you played before. Even the first boss was better than any i encountered in dark souls.- They system itself. If you go greedy, you may get out more rewards, but if you then die, your double-screwed. Very interesing mechanic that goes through the whole game.So, why did i use the word dark souls that often even tho i don´t think it can be seriously compared to it? Because everyone else does! Stop doing that, this game does so much better than dark souls and via the different mechanics, it is difficult to compare these games in other points than the combat system and the ""get your stuff back when your die"".And why did i only give 9 points if i wound everything so enjoyable?Well, you can heal urself over and over again even tho your still fighting the enemies. While none of them are too close to the healing crystal, you can just keep going. A minor flaw in an otherwise super awesome game.High hopes to see more games like this in the future, for now, ima go and play some more..."
76561198027512227,Recommended,265300,20259151,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,The Courier,"I am primarily writing this review to do  my part to improve this game's review score. Many play this game, expecting it to be like Dark Souls, and while this is not untrue, there are two key differences that I have observed in my limited time playing.- The combat is slower. Dodging, attacking, and other aspects of Dark Souls muscle memory must be overcome before you can get far. Dodge early, and you will be able to avoid most attacks.- The story is bluntly presented. Dark Souls presented its story in subtle way, rewarding those who took the time to explore it. This is not the case in ""Lords of the Fallen"", and that is not something I like. The story is also less ""serious"", and more action-hero-oriented. The atmosphere is completely different.In the end, I enjoy playing the game, but it does not provide the experience I had hoped for. However, I still think it is a worthy purchase at $30 or below. I am happy to have given it a chance, and I think people are being hard on the game because they come in with high expectations."
