,Recommended,265300,18555468,"Posted: 18 October, 2015",all,KingCrimson,"Lords of the Fallen is a smooth and beautiful looking game that I saw on the Steam promotion window one day and thought ""Dang, I gotta get my hands on that!"" and then promptly waited for the Summer Sale.There's a lot to be said about this game, so I'll just break it down into the most intersting points:PROS:- Easy to learn, hard to master controls. Simularly done with the Dark Souls games, but less punishing than them.- Diverse build selections add to replayable runs. Different weapons with different class variants make playing the game different each time you want to mix things up.- Combat and bosses are very fun. Fighting in very different scenarios each time you play also adds to the adventure.- Stunning environments. The game looks like if a greco-roman piece got thrown up onto a surrealistic display. The detail is amazing and the entire game is just beautiful.- Enviroment is surprisingly immersive, easy to get lost metaphorically and physically.- Story isn't too complex, but it's very engaging. Makes you work for side information that unveils more of the lore for your own desire to exploreCONS:- You might need a decent rig to run this game. I had no trouble and my PC is just decent to mediocre, but I wouldn't run this on a toaster.- Some parts can be a bit frustrating to take you out of the game's immersion, but to veteran Dark Souls/Demon Souls players and what-not you might really enjoy parts where you bash your head against a wall 20 times until you scratch the first of twenty layers of the 2nd boss' armor, thus proving he can be hurt eventually.- Weapon choices and armor choices seem to be a bit limited at times. This is maily because you get sword, shield, axe, staff, fists, and thats it. Trying to hybrid your build makes for interesting combinations. Playing around with weapons and armor is half the game, but can get dissapointing since there is a very low pool of equipment.- Eventually you find a really cheap and unfair way to just kill opponents (if you're like me) and then spam that technique until you beat the game.- steep price tag wait for the sale tbh famCONCLUSION:Listen, I really, REALLY dig this game. I thought it was fun, immersive, gorgeous to look at, extremely fun, rewarding, and overall a good game. It's not for everyone, and can be a bit tough and tricky at some points, but please give this game a try. I highly recommend it. If you can afford to grab this game when you're cruising this vast sea of cosmos, I cannot stress it hard enough that you should.___________________Pro tips: Put a ton of points into strength, endurance, and vitality. (and luck if you want) Then wear the heavest armor in the game (Lord set) then equip the 'Reminder - one handed axe' (strongest one handed weapon as far as I know) and also the 'Void shield - tower shield'. The strategy here is to run at enemies, then raise your shield, then knock them to the ground. Once they are stuck being floored, beat the living hell out of them with your axe because it's considered fast one handed but still does a ton of damage. I abused this strategy the entire game and it was a lot of fun actually. Don't know the exact numbers, but if you find better equipment then feel free to upgrade."
