76561197972234665,Recommended,265300,15602993,"Posted: 28 April, 2015",all,Flori der Fux,"Lords of the Fallen plays pretty much exactly like Dark Souls. Players of Dark Souls will from the first minute on feel familiar with the controls and the combat system. The game however ain't no German-Polish Dark Souls clone. And I do not recommend comparing too much. Dark Souls is epic, LotF is not, you can easily finish it in 30 or so hours. Dark Souls is a whole lot harder and more challenging, and LotF is much more forgiving and therefore less frustrating for many players. And LotF looks a whole lot better, as the graphics are truely stunning. My suggestion: Don't ask which game is ""better"". I say : if you enjoyed DS, and you are hungry for more stuff of that genre, LotF is for you. If DS was too frustrating for you, or you are new to that genre, LotF is the right game for you to get in touch with the mechanics and game physics. I truely enjoyed playing this game. The many negative reviews mostly have to do with the enormous bunch of bugs at the release and even months after the release of the game. By now, however, it'S save to say that most major bugs have been erased. I've only encountered one while playing through the game (a crash at a boss fight) and solved it by setting PhysX to CPU only and disabling the enhanced nVIDIA physX mode. It's an awesome game, I loved the dark setting, the nice graphics, the DS-feeling without too much frustration, the skill tree, the smooth combat moves. The boss fights could have been more tactical and challenging, okay, it's not a perfect game. It's a GOOD game that I warmly recommend. Don't let all the negative reviews scare you from buying it. I sure didn't regret playing it."
76561198127064019,Not Recommended,265300,15609106,"Posted: 29 April, 2015",all,CybernatonEvolution,"Lords of the Fallen is an action RPG  that had good premise, and intended to implement some of the best combinations of game mechanics and RPG elements; it borrows heavily (in a half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥way) from action-RPG games, but its execution is hurrendous.Major issues with the game:-Gameplay: I will talk about it extensively below.-Performance: the game runs like crap. It has terrible frame-timing and constant frame-rate drops.-Story/lore: the game is simply uninteresting, generic and emphasises on random NPCs that are not properly introduced; the gameplay doesn't make up for it, and I honestly care about gameplay more.-Glitches: Aside from the numerous issues with collision detection, the game has terrible glitches that appear mostly in boss battles; the boss freezing glitch is terrible.Get it when it is for sale or simply ignore it and wait for the sequel.Gameplay:The game has the standard action-RPG approach in gameplay. The player is provided with roll, run, lock-on, weapon-type specific moveset, magic attacks (projectiles, clones,..etc), block and parry. The combination of sluggish controls/input lag, slow roll, run/roll overlapping and impractical weapon/shield/magic switching makes the game absolutely boring and a chore to play.Furthermore, the game is mechanically ****. Enemies have insane startup and tracking, terrible full-body hitboxes and a lot of active frames. Parrying is nearly useless, and rolling is inconsistent and dumb; you need to be nearly naked to make use of it, and it is still risky to use. The previous issues with enemy design and unreliable mechanics brings us to the next issue: balance.The game is unabalanced and has stat-scalling; some low-level mobs suddenly start one-shotting you at some point in the game if you are not leveled up properly. New enemies scale very badly, and force you to use limited viable builds and playstyles that revolve around stat and AI cheesing; new enemies simply hit MUCH harder, take significantly less damage, thus making any technical hit-and-run or flashy parrying useless (you have to break the AI or simply become overpowered).Overall, the game feels unrefined and inconsistent; it is bad on a basic level in terms of mechanics. It runs like crap, and every boss battle is simply bad (the same goes for new mobs). There are a lot of turtling and lack of proper openings from enemies in the game; you don't get rewarded for trying to look for new strategies.I was personally hyped for the game, and I supported it because I like the genre. I would like more games with similar gameplay approach, but without the terrible performance and execution. I have heard that developers are developing a sequel, so get this game on a sale and invest more in providing feedback for the sequel."
