76561198034888313,Not Recommended,265300,15629590,"Posted: 30 April, 2015",all,Sedina,"Lords of the Fallen is a fun game. Sometimes, it's a clever game. But it's really not a very interesting game, and that's where I can't recommend it. Crashes continue to plague the game, six months later. While they have linked a forums post here on Steam to another forum talking about these crashes, it's not even close to enough. Their customers - not the devs, the customers - put together a _massive_ list of all of the problems and a few options for fixes.The world is fairly small - you'll see most of it in the first few hours - though a lot of backtracking is involved. You can choose to play as a tanky damage machine, or a caster, or a quick rogue. Each of the playstyles are different enough to be interesting. Weapons and armor are littered around the game world, and each has a unique appearance. Kudos to their art department.The game is a straightforward action. It's a lot easier than Dark Souls and that's OK. Leveling up your character and picking up better weapons / armor makes a huge difference. Sometimes it's nice to feel powerful. But the bosses and the game overall are too easy; the only times in which I didn't kill a boss on the first try was when the game crashed.And boy does it crash. I have a machine easily capable of running this game, with a brand new install of Windows. No cruft. No video card from Joe's Discount Computer Shack. I run a Titan X on a few i7 cores, etc, etc. Game crashes often enough that I had to give up on it.I don't remember the story because it was generically bad."
