76561198065076193,Recommended,265300,12769368,"Posted: 3 November, 2014",all,^eripsnI,"Everyone is saying that we should put ''apex_gpu_support_enabled'' to ''false'' as it disables the gpu pysx and forces them on the CPU. After doing so I was getting 21-30ish frames on a FX6300 @ 4.6Ghz + R9 270x, unnacceptable. Being the dab hand that I am, I messed with the settings and I found that with the ''apex_gpu_support_enabled'' on true as well as all the ''thread'' settings also on TRUE, I'm able to play with a mix of high/med settings at a constant 50-60 fps which is far more than some 780 ti users can currently say. So just TRY to play with your own setting, you may find that what is working for everyone else may just make your situation worse.The game itself is brilliant, more weighty than dark souls, but in a good way. The level design is also top-notch with some decent little shortcuts and little secrets, not the DaS2 Bonfire>Ememies>Boss>Bonfire, granted I'm only a few hours in at the time of writing.TL;DR : Performance nightmare, but can be fixed - if you can find settings that make it work for you, is actually a cracking game."
