,Recommended,265300,16365510,"Posted: 13 June, 2015",all,Margonite,"IntroductionThis game is constantly seen as a half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥Dark Souls copycat because it takes a lot of similar mechanics from it, but the unfortunate thing is that it is getting a bad rap because they feel the need to express how much they love Dark Souls and how Dark Souls is the greatest game ever played. I love Dark Souls but honestly don't compare these games too hard.GameplayThis is where this game shines honestly, for the first time I have actually played a game and felt like wielding different weapons completely effected how I faught. Seriously the move sets for the weapons deeply reflect various styles of play, so instead of grabbing the biggest weapon you see to one shot mobs you actually might have to find a weapon that is right for you.-for example one person reviewed the game saying the combat was clunky. I think that was the wrong thing to say because weapon styles feel more realistic here, swinging heavy weapons is going to actually feel slow, because they are HEAVY. I would honestly say timing is more important in this game than it is darksouls, except for the fact that monsters do not hit as hard so you dont get punished as much.The spell system is rather small but adds some nice finesse to the different classes. It is more of an avatar system that a spell system so don't expect a lot of glorious magical spells.Graphics and Art StyleThe visuals for this game are done rather well actually. the game looks beautiful but the voice acting needs to be matched up better with the animations. The armor and weapon designs are beautiful but light armors don't portray a light-armor design. Then again, Harkan doesn't really seem like the light-armor type anyway. The game definitely gives you that fantasy sort of feel.One issue with the game is the lack of variety in monsters and explorable areas. Although for the setting you are given there are tons of explorable ground, the world is mostly contained in a monestary and a rhogar realm. have fun getting lost beneath the monestary though.StoryThe story is a bit breif, but is rather interesting. i'm not going to spoil a whole lot of it for you but I will say that I think this game has tons of potential for later games.DLCThe dlc sucks hands-down but the companies that made the game are rather small and most of the dlc was extra incentive to people who pre-ordered the game.SummaryThis is the first game that takes a close look at making people feel like they are wielding different weapons, but with having a rather small group of developers the weapon range excludes bows/ or an advanced magic system. The content is a bit short but is definitely worth a couple plays through and the concepts and ideas show a lot of promise for games to come in this series. I would also like to add that the developers show signs of really wanting to improve on this game so keep a look out for a very promising future."
