76561197967838799,Not Recommended,265300,13622187,"Posted: 26 December, 2014",all,Loqa,"Nice things first - The graphic is realy good. Also the XP-Gain system and the ""reward"" for fighting as long as possible without using checkpoints is realy good. The design of the small armory is very good.And that's it. Nothing more nameable about it.ALSOyou have to know something. I played demon souls, Dark souls I / II. I love these games, even if I hate them in some special way. Therefore I compare this game mostly to dark souls I / II. I think because I like the souls series much, I gave this game hard time. If you are a casual gamer and just want to play a Hack&Slay which looks pretty decent and doesn't care much about anything else- Then Go for it.The Bad things (and why):1. The ambience + story:You are thrown into a world, from which you barely get to know things. Sometimes you find an audio record in which somebody tells something about the place you are. You know nothing about anything at the start, even you. I mean come on - even Dark Souls I/II did better. And even after you get to know a few things about you and the demons you are fighting against, it is misplaced and boring.2. The ""Skilltrees"":You have 3 different classes(cleric, rogue, warrior) witch can choose of 3 skilltrees (warrior, assassin, cleric). Sounds great but every skilltree is made out of just 4 Spells. Every of that Spell can be skilled 3 times. The first spell of every class is the same. You create an Illusion of yourself, which the enemy has to attack...except he is a range enemy. As a warrior, the spellset is pretty useless. Too manai-intense,  too little damage and so on.3. The Enemies:Yeah most of them are pretty easy to defeat and those wo aren't, they are pretty bad. And example - every time I attack an enemy from behind (even when he is distracted by one of my illusions) he turns his front towards me, while I swing the weapon. In most of the times this isn't important, but pretty dumb. When you fight against an enemy with a shield, he will always turn his front towards you and therefore you attack his shield. Even when he is attack an illusion, when I swing the weapon he instantly turns himself towards me (except he is swinging his weapon at my illusion). And now a fun fact : When I block a hit from such an shield enemy and I instantly swing my weapon at him, my weapon hits the shield but makes normal damage. Just because I blocked a hit from him means I can hit him? That's dumb.4. Crafting :Its lifeless and annoying. You have exactly 2 kinds of runes. Small ones and big ones. Once you've found the smith, you can break the runes open and they will get an effect by random. These runes can be placed into your weapons and armorparts. Beside the fact, that there are just 2-3 realy useful runes, after I had the runes that I wanted, all the other runes where obsolete. Sadly you cant do anything else with these runes than crafting (okay thats not entirely true. You can use small ones to open some chests.). So ...you just carry about 20+ small runes with you and will never use them. It would be more fun, if you could combine runes to better runes or something.5. Armory :Yeah that game got some weapons. Most of them are trash and totally worthless. And it seems to be complete irrelevant which rarity these weapons have. E. g. after I finished a boss, I got an orange colored weapon (which I suppose is very rare) and in an instant later I found a totally normal weapon which was better in every aspect. Also you can't get rid of useless weapons and have to carry them around. The most annoying fact is, that you can't realy upgrade weapons. Some of them have sockets and you can put the runes into them...but that's all. Would it be realy THAT hard to develop a system in which I could use runes for forging weapons and upgrade them to the best so that I could use the shortsword I realy like but can't use because its damage output is too low? I think not.6. Attributes:You got Strength, agility, faith, endurance, vitality and luck. Yeah...6 Attributes and 4 Spells. Great. Luck is mostly useless...sooner or later you will find a good weapon of choice and a good armor. And to get better runes...well you got enough runes. For me the game lacks an attribute like a quickness. You can't change the speed in which you are rolling or swinging yourweapons...why?7. The ""Help"" :Yeah..help is nice. If you want to know what the different stats in a weapon mean, you gonna have a bad time. Most of them are self-explaining but let's take the stat ""POWER 100%"". What does it say? Well looking in the internet may help you, but why can't I see it in the game?  Dark souls II could explain EVERY word...why not this game?8. gain & use experience:Well that's something I just personally don't like. Others may find it nice. Because there are so few things to level up, a few points make a recognizable difference. Also this leads to the situation, that after a few hours of gameplay, you'll need to ""farm"" about 30 minutes to just gain 1-2 new level ups. For me this is very frustrating. In Dark Souls II, you reached that point at the end of the first playthrough.So that's all I have to say. I hope it helps you to determine if you will like it or not. It's very simple and has a lot of potential, but sadly unused potential."
