,Recommended,265300,14831905,"Posted: 10 March, 2015",all,Captain jOE,"Lord's of the Fallen. I have to say I greatly enjoyed the game. It's a great ARPG. I really think they ""nailed"" the combat. I loved it! The setting was good. And the end was satisfying. I both had a good adrenaline rush as well as a satisfying end to an epic tale!The atmoshpere of the game was cool. It was very ""short story-ish."" The game isn't huge and expansive but the areas are cohesive and set the setting and story well. This came with a slightly bland line up of enemies, but again, kinda makes sense given the small scale of the game setting.To expand on the combat. It felt very smooth and responsive, the swing times and blocking felt right. Not blindingly fast, not unresponsive like Dark Souls can be at times (love the souls games, but combat has it's hitches). Mixing blocking, attack strengths, shield bashing, gauntlet shots, and magic made the combat interesting, flow well and feel right. The sound effects.... felt soooo right, satisfying crunches. Shield bashing was awesome, as a warrior it really felt like you could manhandle the enemies. It really felt like you were in control of the combat while feeling the right tempo considering how beefy and armored you are.The music was suprisingly good. Not in the music itself as much as the use of it. In Dark Souls you get music pretty much only for bosses and your home campfire. LOTF used it sparingly. Sometimes there was just the howl of the wind. Others, epic operatic scores. It made certain points of the game more tense, it felt urgent and epic.I had a few crashes but only in the audio lore screen, hope that get's cleared up.Pros-Awesome combat-Mix of dialogue and lore was great at conveying the story-Graphics look gorgeous-Cool armor and weapons-Atmosphere: gritty and cohesive-Music-The gauntlet is freakin coolCons-Enemies, little diversity-Sometimes the audio dialogue was stitched together in an awkward way-A few crashes when viewing lore and running backround programs like dxtory-The game sometimes was very vague on sidequest locations, even a sketched map or slightly better npc directions would be great (as you can't review their directions either).First time I've ever written a review. I just wanted to counteract all of the negativity this game is getting. Does it crash at times? Yes. Does it have a few glitches? Yes. But why is it ok for triple A developers to get away with wayyyy more buggy games and it's ""ok"" because we like a franchise. This game was an awesome first game in a franchise I hope to see more games in it. This developer is good and I would like to fund their future endeavors. I just hope in future titles they can clear up a few of the crashing issues and hopefully make larger more diverse games. Although if they wanted to stick with this more focused ""epic/shortstory"" (ancient mythos style) I would be all for it. Hopefully with a slight price drop though."
