,Recommended,265300,12682593,"Posted: 29 October, 2014",all,SnarKs,"After 10 hours.So for all you Souls fans:Game mechanics -I wouldnt approach combat in the sameway that you approach dark souls. Especially if you like to fast roll and rely mostly on dodging instead of a shield to avoid damage. It seems like lords of the fallen is designed with the mindset that you WILL TRADE HITS with enemies. Which seems really horrible if you want to play a lightly armored character in this game, as armor does actually provide excellent damage reduction. A good example of this was when I was fighting the boss in the catacombs. The boss had only one attack that I could dodge and retaliate without being hit. This worked until phase 3 of the fight when he stops doing that attack, and I am pretty much forced to trade hits because the boss recovers from attacks very quickly. Unless of course I am just bad and couldnt see another opportunity to hit him without worry.i-frames - I think theres some invulnrability while rolling, but its doesnt last long. Definitely not the same timing as dark souls. So something else that you would have to adjust too. Ive kinda stopped rolling after that boss in the catacombs.Shield Turtling Enemies - These enemies just feel plain stupid in this game. Although after a while I think Ive gotten a decent tactic to dealing with them. Kicking and then attacking them seems to break their poise very fast. If you just kick them continuously, it takes 3 kicks to get their poise down. Same goes for attacking and bashing. You can also do a sprinting shield charge that breaks their poise everytime.Shortcuts - if you liked opening shortcuts in dark souls, well theres tons of levers in this game that open up doors that connect to previous areas. So far theres no fast travel, lots of back tracking like the first half of dark souls.The game itself -Pretty good so far. The world exploration feels really good. You got your set main path, many side roads to explore. I think the catacombs area is completely optional, and is so far the best area Ive explored.Enemy variety isn't much yet. Mostly youre fighting the rhogar, and the game introduces a new rhogar type enemy once and a while. Theres been a fair amount of giant spiders and demon hounds.Inventory management is terrible. Its just as bad as dark souls, if not worse.Boss fights - Ive only done 4 so far. The first one is a decent first boss right at the start of the game. The second one is meh, graveyard boss is pretty good, and the catacombs boss I dont really know how I feel about. I didnt like being forced to trade hits during the 3rd phase, maybe Im just bad.>.>Devs#1 -"" Hey, lets put PhysX in our game and not put an option in to completely disable all the super demanding PhysX stuff! ""Devs#2- ""Oh YEAH! GOOD IDEA! EVERYBODY WANTS PHYSX STUFF ON!""Devs#4,5,6,7,8,8,786,867,86474756 - ""WHOOOO PHYSX! YEAH!""Nvidia - ""PHYSX! GO F YOURSELF AMD!""P.S. - I have an Nvidia card. And the devs have just updated it with the option to disable physx in the menu."
