,Not Recommended,265300,12757079,"Posted: 2 November, 2014",all,neojb1989,"--- Post Post Post Patch Edit Edit Edit ---Addition...the game still crashes with the removal of those settings, but atleast it's only a crash to desktop now and not a crash of my entire computer. I don't know anymore. It's just...how does a game in this state make it through to a full release? Even people on consoles are having difficulties!Make your decision, the game itself is fun, when it works.---Post Post Patch Edit Edit---In the advanced settings of the graphics, there are three columns. If you disable/low all the columns on the right hand side, the game seems to be permantly stable. It's unfortunate because those make the game look very pretty but, stability over graphics anyday. Changing it back to a game I recommend playing with the frustruation of crashes now gone, I can enjoy it without going crazy whenever I lose progress to a crash.---Post Patch Edit---Before the patch, the game would crash, the screen would flicker, the screen would show an image again and I could continue on using my comp by simply closing the game. This new patch kills the image to my monitor and I have to restart my computer because I can't see anything. I want to enjoy this game because it looks great and is fun but ♥♥♥♥ man, I can't get past it just crashing my computer completey.I bought it after watching VatiVidya's video on it and everything he said about the game is true, but ♥♥♥♥ man...how does something this crashy get released and past testers?--- ---(TL:DR)-Game crashes alot. Sometimes at the worst times, setting you back very far (worst was an hour for me). If that weren't an issue, this game would be great. Buy it but get ready for frustration.Before I fought the second to last boss, I had to wait and hear some dialogue while my previous boss kills were shown to me , alongside with the weapon I used to kill them, how long it took, and how many attempts. This whole thing took about 10 minutes to 15 minutes.Halfway through that next boss fight, one of the bosses hit me with a flame attack while I was blocking with the gauntlet and my game crashed.Since the game only saves the state whenever you hit a checkpoint or go through to a major zone, I got reset to before the 15 minute dialogue.The game, in the state that it is in on 11/2/2014, is broken just enough where, when it does crash, it is extremely infuriating.One of the mechanics in the game is, the longer you go without hitting a checkpoint, the better drop rate and experience you'll gain. This would work FANTASTICALLY if the game never had any real threat of crashing. But since it does crash frequently, and the game only saves on checkpoints or on entering a major story zone, you can very easily loose an hour of progress just because you were trying to raise your experience/item multiplier by not hitting every checkpoint.This happened to me multiple times and the most infuriating is when it happens after a boss fight or after sitting through a bunch of dialogue or finding a key item. It's just ♥♥♥♥♥♥, real ♥♥♥♥♥♥.The thing is though, I can't say how I'd review the game if this never occured because I'm just a bit salty over the whole thing. The game itself is solid, it's souls-like, it's generally easier than dark souls or demon souls, the design is much more fantasy and bright and none of that is bad. The combat has some nice mechanics (with the timing aspect and whatnot) but the bosses are a little simple.You can make the game quite easy for yourself by making sure to level up your health and then stick to one main damage dealing stat (maybe a little faith for your gauntlet and spells, atleast to the point where you can use all your class spells) and you'll likely never have a problem. Pay attention to any buff icons that might appear on your character, because some class spells don't mention specific buffs (for example in the blue spells, the 'shelter' spell will actually heal you although that is not mentioned in the description).I don't know, the game is fun, it looks good, it plays well, it's fairly short (not counting crashes, someone coming from a dark souls or demon souls will easily beat the game in under 10 hours) and there's some replayability in trying out different classes. Though I hear new game + is lackluster.I haven't beat the game because having just crashed at the 2nd to last boss I'm just frustrated. I would have no second though recommending this game IF IT WASN'T SO BUGGY! I'll still say 'yes', in the hopes that at some point the issues are fixed but just be warned, this game is buggy and it can lead to some real bad frustration."
