76561198024930818,Recommended,265300,13679355,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,ZanderJS,"Updating my review, now that I've completed the game.For those who have played the Souls games, you may find LOTF to be somewhat slower, less responsive in that your movements are sluggish, be it evasion, recovering from attacks or casting spells. Plus side though, is that it's a smaller world IMHO, so it's a little bit faster to finish it.Control wise, I can only comment that you are better off using a controller, as with the Souls games. With it, it's quite okay.However, you will need to take note of your own handling of the control when it comes to running and evasion. Running here uses the L3 button, so that has a tendency to sometimes work or not work in the heat of battle. So happens one of the key attacks in this game is a running jump attack, allowing you to close the distance and whack during an opening, and openings are a tad hard to come by in this game.As for Evasion, it uses the A button (Xbox 360 for PC controller) and the button also doubles up as the sprint jump button. Hence, you need to make sure you are not running in order to pull off a proper roll.Weapon setup wise, I don't find LOTF to be very balanced. Unlike Souls, you practically need a shield, both for breaking down walls to hidden areas as well as to stagger shield-bearing opponents (Rhogar Bulwarks). The kick in this game doesn't help with breaking shield guards, thereby rendering your two-handed moveset pointless in such a fight. For dual-wielders, you can't really out-circle strafe the shielders. Hence, the game creates much frustration if you do not wield a shield.And for those who fancy using Magic only, look elsewhere.Spells here are only to support melee and they are terribly slow to cast, often preventing you from pulling one off successfully in the heat of battle.Range damage comes in the form of The Gauntlet, which is a magic arm cannon.Doesn't do much damage but does provide some effects with the use of different runes.Hence, you WILL need to rely on Melee.Bad points aside, the game does have good graphics and some of the elements it has are pretty good ideas:1. The Combo-Timing System2. The EXP Modifier Streak / EXP banking System3. The non-respawning of enemies when using the recovery crystal/savepoint.4. The ability to save without resetting your XP Modifier.Story wise, it feels a bit weak, especially since you have no idea about Harkyn's (the main character) background.Overall though, I guess it's not too bad a game, but ultimately I suggest to get this while it's on a good  discount."
