76561198064388679,Recommended,265300,33790147,Posted: 25 July,all,ZenZone1,"TL;DRIt was worth it - for me, and i hope it would be too for you if you give it more time.Main reviewNormally the first thing i do is check the GPU and CPU requirements; if no AMD is listed i would immediately skip it and move on. This one made me pause to take a closer look because it was discounted heavily. After perusing the forum discussions, it was apparent that it had problems with both Nvidia and AMD GPUs, yet some AMD users reported it runs fine so i took a calculated low-risk purchase of it.Lots of talk about it being clunky and slow. Well it was perceived that way for the most part when i started, being used to immediate response and animations which can be interrupted at will. Well not this one, once clicked you had to follow through so timing of strikes and blocks are crucial and has to be done with a keen eye of the opponent and the other on your energy reserve. Well not one eye here and one eye there really but you need good peripheral vision.The combat system while being frequently describe as slow is due to 2 things; weight of gear and weapons, AND realistically it takes time to move from one stance to another; there's no luxury of frame skip or time skip where you can switch motion and animation instantly. Remember you expend energy on every motion and quickly mashing buttons will exhaust your hero to the point thathe is too tired to swing so he just stands there waiting for another, hopefully smarter key input. There's no luxury of time dilation either where everything slows but you. So yeah i think combat is as realistic as it gets.Update 2 July 26 2028hrsMy bad depleting energy reserves does not disable ability to strike, only to dodge or run. The reason for not being able to move is due to enemy's strong attack; it may stun or stagger thereby causing momentary immobility.End of Update ...As can be inferred in previous paragraphs, you can probably see that LOTF can be both hard and easy depending on how you play it. Grinding in order to level-up and farming for loot may be required in order to progress. Key points; save energy and mana or as is called in the game 'magic energy'. Patience, don't look for easy kill on the bosses unless you've grinded too much in your backtracking.Why is this game easy? Ordinary enemies wait for you, they don't hunt you down even when you're well within visual range unless you shoot/strike first. Plus there is an easy stealth mode where you can sneak-up behind an enemy and perform special kills; heavy boots or armor clunky clangs are not taken into account. There is also a rush and bash technique to knock your opponent down or shoot from afar with a range weapon to wear down your enemies or lure it closer for a finishing blow. Bosses need to be handled with good tactics; plus being at the right level helps a lot. Bosses can be really hard until you figure out what works.So yeah, it's hard, it's easy and there's a lot of farming for loot in the process. There's crafting later in the game that allows you to improve your gear but i haven't reached that stage yet; you need to find an NPC to unlock that feature.SummaryRuns smooth but changing screen resolution for the first time may cause it to cycle modes endlessly while flickering at a fraction of a second. No glitch or crash encountered during play. Only one time it freezes for a few seconds during combat then resumed normally.Graphics - 9Sound effects - 9Music - 8Story - Dunno i wasn't attentiveVoice acting - 8Cut scenes - 98.5/10 in my book. Never tried Mortal Kombat yet but this looks and feel like a real mortal combat should. This not a typical Action-RPG, its combat near simulation level.Update 1Stability - 7 It crashes when cleric tries to switch to fast rogue weapons like daggers. Correction: This crash appears 2b random & unrepeatable.Score dropped to 8/10Update 2 July 26 2017, 2033hrsStability 6 - Random crashes. Game throws me out to desktop for the 2nd time when i was winning a boss fight. What gives? Demon not happy?Score dropped to 7/10Update 3 - July 27, 2017, 0135hrsStability 5 - For the 3rd time i got dumped to desktop while i was winning the boss fight. The Worshipper had only 1½ segment of life left while i had full. WTF! It's demon envy alright.Score reduced to 6/10. I have a feeling this game is about to get a thumbs down from me."
